1
00:00:41,984 --> 00:00:44,623
(I like mountains and spacing out.)

2
00:00:44,624 --> 00:00:46,664
(I also like driving!)

3
00:00:49,556 --> 00:00:54,326
(Actress Kim Tae Ri)

4
00:00:58,034 --> 00:01:02,173
(I'm currently doing something...)

5
00:01:02,174 --> 00:01:05,973
(for the first time...)

6
00:01:05,974 --> 00:01:09,684
(in my life!)

7
00:01:10,344 --> 00:01:13,354
I first acted...

8
00:01:13,554 --> 00:01:15,584
in college.

9
00:01:18,024 --> 00:01:19,084
Back then,

10
00:01:21,454 --> 00:01:25,094
the joy I felt left a deep impression,

11
00:01:25,464 --> 00:01:28,364
which made me want to become an actress.

12
00:01:30,104 --> 00:01:32,634
To me, acting...

13
00:01:34,534 --> 00:01:36,574
is always special.

14
00:01:38,304 --> 00:01:39,944
I can't forget the moment...

15
00:01:40,314 --> 00:01:43,343
the audience applauded...

16
00:01:43,344 --> 00:01:44,784
after I took...

17
00:01:45,514 --> 00:01:48,014
the stage for the first time.

18
00:01:50,524 --> 00:01:51,624
That's why...

19
00:01:52,954 --> 00:01:58,023
(This time, I've decided to become a teacher.)

20
00:01:58,024 --> 00:02:00,233
(And today,)

21
00:02:00,234 --> 00:02:06,704
(I'm meeting my first students.)

22
00:02:13,674 --> 00:02:17,214
(Embraced by the ridges of the Sobaek Mountains)

23
00:02:18,084 --> 00:02:20,683
I'm in Mungyeong. Amazing.

24
00:02:20,684 --> 00:02:21,884
(Mungyeong)

25
00:02:22,414 --> 00:02:23,524
Just look at the mountains.

26
00:02:23,554 --> 00:02:24,884
It's fall everywhere.

27
00:02:25,954 --> 00:02:27,124
How pretty.

28
00:02:28,454 --> 00:02:32,093
(A small village surrounded by many mountains)

29
00:02:32,094 --> 00:02:33,493
(Stick with me, my friend!)

30
00:02:33,494 --> 00:02:35,493
(With teamwork, we can achieve so much more!)

31
00:02:35,494 --> 00:02:37,104
(Yongheung Elementary School)

32
00:02:38,164 --> 00:02:40,004
"Yongheung Elementary School."

33
00:02:44,144 --> 00:02:45,504
Can I walk across the field?

34
00:02:49,614 --> 00:02:52,114
The kids play on the field, so it should be fine, right?

35
00:02:55,414 --> 00:02:58,054
(Entering Yongheung Elementary School)

36
00:02:58,454 --> 00:02:59,824
The school is so cute.

37
00:03:00,894 --> 00:03:03,794
Walking to the school made me feel huge.

38
00:03:05,124 --> 00:03:06,324
I'm a giant.

39
00:03:07,234 --> 00:03:10,463
As a fully grown adult,

40
00:03:10,464 --> 00:03:12,364
it felt like walking on sacred ground.

41
00:03:13,674 --> 00:03:14,833
A cat!

42
00:03:14,834 --> 00:03:17,304
(Welcome.)

43
00:03:17,774 --> 00:03:19,044
"Principal's office."

44
00:03:19,544 --> 00:03:20,544
"Principal's office."

45
00:03:22,144 --> 00:03:23,684
Yes, come in.

46
00:03:23,914 --> 00:03:26,713
- Hi.
- Hi.

47
00:03:26,714 --> 00:03:28,453
- Take a seat over here.
- Okay.

48
00:03:28,454 --> 00:03:30,123
Thank you for coming all the way here.

49
00:03:30,124 --> 00:03:32,023
Don't worry about it. Did you wait for long?

50
00:03:32,024 --> 00:03:33,053
- No.
- No.

51
00:03:33,054 --> 00:03:34,293
(Principal's Office, Administrative Consultation Room)

52
00:03:34,294 --> 00:03:35,453
Nice to meet you.

53
00:03:35,454 --> 00:03:38,463
- My name is Kim Tae Ri.
- I see.

54
00:03:38,464 --> 00:03:42,034
I'm the teacher in charge of the after-school acting class.

55
00:03:42,864 --> 00:03:44,503
(Being a "teacher" is still awkward.)

56
00:03:44,504 --> 00:03:47,633
What did you think while walking to our school?

57
00:03:47,634 --> 00:03:49,003
It's so cute and pretty.

58
00:03:49,004 --> 00:03:50,743
- Isn't it?
- Yes.

59
00:03:50,744 --> 00:03:54,173
We have 18 students at our school.

60
00:03:54,174 --> 00:03:56,243
- Right.
- It's a very small school.

61
00:03:56,244 --> 00:03:57,484
(A small school with 18 students)

62
00:04:00,184 --> 00:04:01,853
Do the students live nearby?

63
00:04:01,854 --> 00:04:04,683
- There are tall mountains around.
- Right.

64
00:04:04,684 --> 00:04:07,393
Each valley has a village.

65
00:04:07,394 --> 00:04:09,093
- The school bus goes around...
- Yes?

66
00:04:09,094 --> 00:04:10,363
picking the students up.

67
00:04:10,364 --> 00:04:11,693
- I see.
- Yes.

68
00:04:11,694 --> 00:04:13,193
(The students get to school by school bus.)

69
00:04:13,194 --> 00:04:15,163
Wait for me.

70
00:04:15,164 --> 00:04:16,634
I ride a bicycle.

71
00:04:17,204 --> 00:04:19,033
To get to a friend's house...

72
00:04:19,034 --> 00:04:20,173
- An hour.
- It takes an hour.

73
00:04:20,174 --> 00:04:21,304
An hour?

74
00:04:21,474 --> 00:04:23,744
We break the ice when the valley freezes.

75
00:04:23,904 --> 00:04:24,974
We drop something on it.

76
00:04:25,144 --> 00:04:29,213
Because it's the countryside, the air is fresh.

77
00:04:29,214 --> 00:04:30,413
(Best things about our school)

78
00:04:30,414 --> 00:04:32,884
See the tall mountains?

79
00:04:33,084 --> 00:04:35,714
When the leaves turn red, looking at them makes me happy.

80
00:04:36,484 --> 00:04:39,824
Our field is natural grass.

81
00:04:40,054 --> 00:04:42,153
- It snows a ton during winter.
- One,

82
00:04:42,154 --> 00:04:44,394
- two, three.
- I can make snowmen with my friend.

83
00:04:44,924 --> 00:04:46,294
We rarely fight.

84
00:04:46,564 --> 00:04:48,734
And many times, we make up quickly.

85
00:04:49,194 --> 00:04:51,704
That's because we might grow apart.

86
00:04:51,864 --> 00:04:55,004
Then we wouldn't have friends to hang out with.

87
00:04:55,104 --> 00:04:57,243
"Dear Sejong the Great."

88
00:04:57,244 --> 00:04:58,873
Yes, I know.

89
00:04:58,874 --> 00:05:00,913
(Everyone in Yongheung Elementary School is close friends.)

90
00:05:00,914 --> 00:05:03,343
- Did you buy elevator shoes?
- No.

91
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:06,013
(Even close with the teacher)

92
00:05:06,014 --> 00:05:09,113
We have such a pretty school in the countryside,

93
00:05:09,114 --> 00:05:13,294
but honestly, you never know when it might close.

94
00:05:13,894 --> 00:05:17,524
We have no new students this year, so there are no first graders.

95
00:05:17,994 --> 00:05:20,393
At this rate, our school might close...

96
00:05:20,394 --> 00:05:22,063
within 3 to 4 years.

97
00:05:22,064 --> 00:05:25,003
That's right. If that happens,

98
00:05:25,004 --> 00:05:28,634
our students' school will disappear.

99
00:05:28,704 --> 00:05:30,073
- I see.
- Yes.

100
00:05:30,074 --> 00:05:31,074
(The students' school might disappear.)

101
00:05:31,674 --> 00:05:33,374
The whole school...

102
00:05:33,944 --> 00:05:36,914
is decorated with things made by the students.

103
00:05:37,184 --> 00:05:40,653
But all those memories disappearing...

104
00:05:40,654 --> 00:05:42,654
would be very sad.

105
00:05:44,084 --> 00:05:46,523
What's more, the villagers...

106
00:05:46,524 --> 00:05:48,423
who were born, raised,

107
00:05:48,424 --> 00:05:50,893
and attended school here...

108
00:05:50,894 --> 00:05:52,723
would find it heartbreaking.

109
00:05:52,724 --> 00:05:54,364
(The villagers will feel empty.)

110
00:05:56,164 --> 00:05:57,663
Run, Won Jun.

111
00:05:57,664 --> 00:06:02,474
(If the school where the students played disappears,)

112
00:06:04,944 --> 00:06:10,614
(even the village's liveliness might disappear too.)

113
00:06:13,984 --> 00:06:17,123
To be frank, life goes on.

114
00:06:17,124 --> 00:06:20,654
Life goes on as the world changes.

115
00:06:22,024 --> 00:06:25,493
(Can I be helpful in this reality?)

116
00:06:25,494 --> 00:06:28,733
Realistically, I think it'll be hard.

117
00:06:28,734 --> 00:06:31,663
Being helpful might not be possible.

118
00:06:31,664 --> 00:06:34,834
That was what I thought, but it still moved me.

119
00:06:35,834 --> 00:06:39,343
Honestly, we're not doing something that has a clear answer.

120
00:06:39,344 --> 00:06:40,773
(Despite it being an unknown path)

121
00:06:40,774 --> 00:06:43,544
It felt like an important moment...

122
00:06:43,644 --> 00:06:46,144
that I shouldn't miss.

123
00:06:47,054 --> 00:06:48,653
I wanted to go for it.

124
00:06:48,654 --> 00:06:50,123
Of course, it won't be easy.

125
00:06:50,124 --> 00:06:52,583
But thinking it might be fun...

126
00:06:52,584 --> 00:06:55,394
played a big part.

127
00:06:56,824 --> 00:07:00,434
(And so, Tae Ri came to Yongheung Elementary School.)

128
00:07:00,964 --> 00:07:04,333
You're here to teach acting, right?

129
00:07:04,334 --> 00:07:06,033
- Correct.
- Right. Our students...

130
00:07:06,034 --> 00:07:07,903
will be acting for the very first time.

131
00:07:07,904 --> 00:07:08,904
- Is that so?
- Yes.

132
00:07:08,905 --> 00:07:09,933
There were no after-school classes?

133
00:07:09,934 --> 00:07:10,973
No.

134
00:07:10,974 --> 00:07:15,013
Since our school is far from downtown Mungyeong...

135
00:07:15,014 --> 00:07:19,113
and it takes about 15 minutes to get here,

136
00:07:19,114 --> 00:07:21,613
it's hard to find any teachers.

137
00:07:21,614 --> 00:07:22,783
(Impossible to find an acting teacher)

138
00:07:22,784 --> 00:07:25,183
That's the kind of situation we're in.

139
00:07:25,184 --> 00:07:27,593
If you, Ms. Kim,

140
00:07:27,594 --> 00:07:29,223
- Yes?
- could teach acting...

141
00:07:29,224 --> 00:07:31,063
- Right.
- to our students,

142
00:07:31,064 --> 00:07:34,593
it would mean so much to them...

143
00:07:34,594 --> 00:07:36,663
- Of course.
- and create unforgettable memories.

144
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:37,833
(It will be an unforgettable memory and experience.)

145
00:07:37,834 --> 00:07:41,603
If you look here, we have seven students...

146
00:07:41,604 --> 00:07:43,003
- in the acting class.
- Right.

147
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:44,143
There are five male students...

148
00:07:44,144 --> 00:07:47,044
- and two female students.
- I see.

149
00:07:47,274 --> 00:07:50,943
And here is a floor plan of our school.

150
00:07:50,944 --> 00:07:52,214
- How cute.
- Right?

151
00:07:53,344 --> 00:07:56,253
You will teach in the gym.

152
00:07:56,254 --> 00:07:57,323
Okay, got it.

153
00:07:57,324 --> 00:07:58,324
(The acting classroom is the gym.)

154
00:07:58,325 --> 00:08:00,923
Then I'll have a look at the classroom.

155
00:08:00,924 --> 00:08:01,993
- Okay, take care.
- Yes.

156
00:08:01,994 --> 00:08:03,224
- Thank you.
- Bye.

157
00:08:12,464 --> 00:08:13,633
"Sesol Hall."

158
00:08:13,634 --> 00:08:15,473
(Arrived at the acting classroom)

159
00:08:15,474 --> 00:08:16,534
"Sesol Hall."

160
00:08:30,284 --> 00:08:33,284
(Introducing the acting classroom)

161
00:08:38,064 --> 00:08:39,923
(When the lights turn on...)

162
00:08:39,924 --> 00:08:42,094
(and the curtain opens,)

163
00:08:43,504 --> 00:08:46,303
(a very special acting class begins.)

164
00:08:46,304 --> 00:08:48,474
Really, it's unbelievable.

165
00:08:48,974 --> 00:08:50,244
My gosh.

166
00:08:53,744 --> 00:08:55,274
Cute.

167
00:08:56,884 --> 00:08:59,114
(Right up her street)

168
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:04,584
My goodness.

169
00:09:05,354 --> 00:09:06,554
Is this a blackboard?

170
00:09:09,894 --> 00:09:13,324
(A huge blackboard)

171
00:09:14,494 --> 00:09:15,893
(Everything she wanted is here.)

172
00:09:15,894 --> 00:09:17,134
For real?

173
00:09:18,234 --> 00:09:19,304
My gosh.

174
00:09:19,634 --> 00:09:21,133
(On one side of the classroom)

175
00:09:21,134 --> 00:09:22,234
Awesome.

176
00:09:25,144 --> 00:09:28,044
(A lounge exclusively for the students)

177
00:09:29,514 --> 00:09:30,744
How cozy.

178
00:09:31,414 --> 00:09:32,584
Oh, my.

179
00:09:33,554 --> 00:09:34,614
Oh, gosh.

180
00:09:34,884 --> 00:09:37,353
It's so cozy in here. I love it.

181
00:09:37,354 --> 00:09:38,354
(Expecting a fierce competition)

182
00:09:39,054 --> 00:09:40,193
Okay.

183
00:09:40,194 --> 00:09:41,223
(Acting class starts tomorrow.)

184
00:09:41,224 --> 00:09:42,524
Okay.

185
00:09:47,494 --> 00:09:48,594
At 2:30pm?

186
00:09:50,964 --> 00:09:52,963
(Here are the acting class students...)

187
00:09:52,964 --> 00:09:56,734
(who will come in through the door tomorrow.)

188
00:09:56,874 --> 00:10:01,374
I'm Jang Won Jin in Grade 3, Class 1 of Yongheung Elementary School.

189
00:10:02,114 --> 00:10:03,473
- Rawr!
- Yipe!

190
00:10:03,474 --> 00:10:06,243
As you can see, I have brown hair.

191
00:10:06,244 --> 00:10:07,684
(His natural brown hair is his charm.)

192
00:10:08,214 --> 00:10:11,024
(Specialty: Copies anything and everything)

193
00:10:11,824 --> 00:10:14,154
(Won Jin, the face of a thousand expressions)

194
00:10:16,294 --> 00:10:20,124
Hi. My name is Lee Eun Soo.

195
00:10:20,394 --> 00:10:22,734
I'm nine years old.

196
00:10:23,934 --> 00:10:25,764
(Totally camera-ready)

197
00:10:26,434 --> 00:10:29,204
I was rich before becoming penniless.

198
00:10:30,604 --> 00:10:34,114
(Perfect score in acting)

199
00:10:35,274 --> 00:10:36,773
(Eun Soo, Yongheung Elementary School's superstar)

200
00:10:36,774 --> 00:10:38,714
In Grade 2, Class 1,

201
00:10:38,884 --> 00:10:40,584
I'm Kim Kyung Mo.

202
00:10:41,684 --> 00:10:44,024
(Expressions as marvelous as the Galaxy)

203
00:10:44,854 --> 00:10:46,384
(My tail is right here.)

204
00:10:46,624 --> 00:10:47,854
(Cute!)

205
00:10:48,924 --> 00:10:50,194
(Innately bright)

206
00:10:50,364 --> 00:10:52,293
I love you!

207
00:10:52,294 --> 00:10:54,364
(Kyung Mo, the youngest cutie)

208
00:10:54,434 --> 00:10:57,003
Enough.

209
00:10:57,004 --> 00:10:58,163
How many times will you kiss me?

210
00:10:58,164 --> 00:11:00,604
In Grade 5, Class 1, I'm Kim Do Hyun.

211
00:11:01,074 --> 00:11:04,104
- We're brothers.
- Brothers.

212
00:11:04,844 --> 00:11:06,874
(His younger brother is always his top priority.)

213
00:11:07,044 --> 00:11:08,343
How about a little bit higher?

214
00:11:08,344 --> 00:11:10,914
(He's an undoubtedly reliable big brother.)

215
00:11:12,084 --> 00:11:13,914
(Quite a crybaby)

216
00:11:14,814 --> 00:11:16,954
(Do Hyun, the acting class's crybaby)

217
00:11:18,024 --> 00:11:20,084
(Turn off your tear faucet.)

218
00:11:20,154 --> 00:11:21,553
In Grade Four at Yongheung Elementary School,

219
00:11:21,554 --> 00:11:22,724
I'm Lee Ju Eun.

220
00:11:23,864 --> 00:11:24,893
(Shy)

221
00:11:24,894 --> 00:11:25,964
The library...

222
00:11:26,594 --> 00:11:28,364
(Usually very shy)

223
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:32,964
(But she's a completely different person on stage.)

224
00:11:33,804 --> 00:11:35,704
(Ju Eun, a skilled actress with unexpected charm)

225
00:11:35,904 --> 00:11:37,873
Hi. In Grade 4, Class 1,

226
00:11:37,874 --> 00:11:39,304
I'm Noh Hyo Min.

227
00:11:40,444 --> 00:11:41,874
(Full of competitive spirit)

228
00:11:42,574 --> 00:11:44,114
(Filled with upsetting incidents)

229
00:11:44,184 --> 00:11:45,184
But...

230
00:11:45,944 --> 00:11:48,254
(An adolescent boy who whines a lot,)

231
00:11:49,014 --> 00:11:51,084
(but takes care of the younger ones behind the scenes)

232
00:11:52,384 --> 00:11:54,324
(Hyo Min, a tough yet warm-hearted 4th grader)

233
00:11:55,754 --> 00:11:57,724
How about introducing yourself?

234
00:11:58,964 --> 00:12:01,264
(Well...)

235
00:12:03,664 --> 00:12:05,403
(Cho Ha Yun, Grade 5)

236
00:12:05,404 --> 00:12:07,073
(Characteristic: Incredibly shy)

237
00:12:07,074 --> 00:12:09,204
Should we do this a bit later?

238
00:12:09,804 --> 00:12:10,804
Yes.

239
00:12:19,844 --> 00:12:24,984
(Will Ha Yun be able to go on stage without a hitch?)

240
00:12:26,154 --> 00:12:28,924
(Before the first class)

241
00:12:29,624 --> 00:12:30,963
I just do it.

242
00:12:30,964 --> 00:12:31,994
(With shyness for some)

243
00:12:32,394 --> 00:12:36,164
We have an acting class today, and I'm excited.

244
00:12:36,294 --> 00:12:38,134
I'm curious about what we'll do.

245
00:12:38,634 --> 00:12:40,033
I can totally ace it!

246
00:12:40,034 --> 00:12:41,234
(With confidence for some)

247
00:12:42,634 --> 00:12:45,173
(With different feelings and expectations)

248
00:12:45,174 --> 00:12:47,243
I think it'll be fun, tough,

249
00:12:47,244 --> 00:12:48,414
and scary.

250
00:12:49,414 --> 00:12:50,583
Ms. Kim!

251
00:12:50,584 --> 00:12:52,084
(Ms. Kim! Come over here!)

252
00:12:52,544 --> 00:12:55,654
(With the students who rely heavily on Ms. Kim,)

253
00:12:56,654 --> 00:12:59,724
(the 17-day-long journey will soon begin.)

254
00:13:10,834 --> 00:13:11,934
It's 9:30am.

255
00:13:16,274 --> 00:13:17,373
It's 9:30am?

256
00:13:17,374 --> 00:13:20,474
(9:30am?)

257
00:13:22,174 --> 00:13:23,213
What?

258
00:13:23,214 --> 00:13:27,484
(Where Ms. Kim has woken up 5 hours before the 1st class)

259
00:13:29,884 --> 00:13:33,854
(Open the door, and there's another room.)

260
00:13:35,924 --> 00:13:37,624
This is hard to believe.

261
00:13:41,034 --> 00:13:43,363
(When you look outside after opening the window,)

262
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:45,163
(Peeking out)

263
00:13:45,164 --> 00:13:46,763
(When you look outside after opening the window,)

264
00:13:46,764 --> 00:13:48,973
(there's the school?)

265
00:13:48,974 --> 00:13:52,003
Where you'll be staying is behind the gym.

266
00:13:52,004 --> 00:13:53,873
(Field, Main building 2nd floor)

267
00:13:53,874 --> 00:13:55,413
- It's this close?
- Yes.

268
00:13:55,414 --> 00:13:56,773
(Ms. Kim's house)

269
00:13:56,774 --> 00:13:57,884
Hold on.

270
00:13:58,744 --> 00:14:00,043
It's really close.

271
00:14:00,044 --> 00:14:02,254
(Literally living close to work)

272
00:14:03,614 --> 00:14:05,923
(With a big yard,)

273
00:14:05,924 --> 00:14:08,154
(there's a mushroom-shaped house.)

274
00:14:09,524 --> 00:14:12,794
(The so-called Mushroom House)

275
00:14:13,864 --> 00:14:16,334
(When you walk across the room,)

276
00:14:18,804 --> 00:14:22,133
(and there is a cozy living room...)

277
00:14:22,134 --> 00:14:23,774
(and a kitchen.)

278
00:14:25,704 --> 00:14:29,273
(The Mushroom House is still quiet.)

279
00:14:29,274 --> 00:14:31,084
(What will happen from now on?)

280
00:14:31,544 --> 00:14:33,413
(Cooking...)

281
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:36,014
(quite well)

282
00:14:36,614 --> 00:14:38,484
(Digging in)

283
00:14:39,284 --> 00:14:40,794
(Digging in?)

284
00:14:41,494 --> 00:14:43,693
(Here he comes.)

285
00:14:43,694 --> 00:14:44,994
It's too cooked.

286
00:14:45,264 --> 00:14:47,294
(A cooking contest is coming soon!)

287
00:14:48,194 --> 00:14:49,964
(And in the yard)

288
00:14:50,704 --> 00:14:51,833
(Lying down)

289
00:14:51,834 --> 00:14:53,204
Nice. It looks good.

290
00:14:53,704 --> 00:14:55,274
(Having barbecues)

291
00:14:55,974 --> 00:14:57,644
(Holding parties)

292
00:14:58,444 --> 00:15:00,304
(And even camping)

293
00:15:01,014 --> 00:15:03,473
- What?
- For real?

294
00:15:03,474 --> 00:15:06,943
(Filled with all sorts of incidents and accidents,)

295
00:15:06,944 --> 00:15:10,254
(as well as laughter)

296
00:15:11,524 --> 00:15:14,994
(The Mushroom House, which has everything, is open.)

297
00:15:15,724 --> 00:15:17,223
(Where's the bathroom?)

298
00:15:17,224 --> 00:15:18,824
(There's no bathroom.)

299
00:15:19,064 --> 00:15:20,293
Where's the bathroom?

300
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:24,664
(But this house is missing one thing.)

301
00:15:25,764 --> 00:15:27,934
(It's the dressing room.)

302
00:15:28,804 --> 00:15:31,873
(Even Ms. Kim looked around for it yesterday.)

303
00:15:31,874 --> 00:15:33,574
I didn't find any bathroom.

304
00:15:34,244 --> 00:15:35,544
Was there a bathroom?

305
00:15:37,284 --> 00:15:38,314
Don't tell me...

306
00:15:39,784 --> 00:15:40,914
No, right?

307
00:15:41,154 --> 00:15:42,814
No way.

308
00:15:45,024 --> 00:15:46,354
It can't be real.

309
00:15:48,554 --> 00:15:50,563
Really, it's not right.

310
00:15:50,564 --> 00:15:51,594
(Where's the bathroom?)

311
00:15:56,064 --> 00:15:58,604
This is so not right!

312
00:16:00,904 --> 00:16:03,004
It's really... Seriously.

313
00:16:05,104 --> 00:16:07,104
(Walking across the big yard)

314
00:16:07,374 --> 00:16:09,014
This is shocking.

315
00:16:10,144 --> 00:16:13,513
(Bathroom)

316
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:15,454
Stop lying to me.

317
00:16:17,384 --> 00:16:19,353
This isn't right at all.

318
00:16:19,354 --> 00:16:21,054
(Extremely far away)

319
00:16:21,654 --> 00:16:22,693
What...

320
00:16:22,694 --> 00:16:24,724
(Laughing)

321
00:16:26,264 --> 00:16:28,493
(Laughing)

322
00:16:28,494 --> 00:16:30,933
(After the overwhelming first encounter)

323
00:16:30,934 --> 00:16:31,934
Okay.

324
00:16:33,234 --> 00:16:34,234
All right.

325
00:16:34,235 --> 00:16:35,704
(Even while unpacking)

326
00:16:36,404 --> 00:16:38,804
Seriously, to go to the bathroom,

327
00:16:41,374 --> 00:16:43,473
I have to get dressed again and leave the house.

328
00:16:43,474 --> 00:16:44,843
(She has to leave the house again.)

329
00:16:44,844 --> 00:16:45,883
For real?

330
00:16:45,884 --> 00:16:47,014
(Up to this point)

331
00:16:50,214 --> 00:16:54,094
(Walking over again)

332
00:16:55,394 --> 00:16:57,424
(She's still excited so far.)

333
00:16:57,994 --> 00:16:59,723
I have to finish it before bed.

334
00:16:59,724 --> 00:17:01,334
(Her trip was a success.)

335
00:17:02,434 --> 00:17:03,434
Seriously.

336
00:17:04,104 --> 00:17:06,304
I left my phone behind.

337
00:17:06,964 --> 00:17:09,474
This is what I hate, you know?

338
00:17:09,974 --> 00:17:13,744
(Off to the bathroom again)

339
00:17:13,974 --> 00:17:16,014
To think I have to walk over there to wash up.

340
00:17:16,714 --> 00:17:18,513
Unbelievable. Really.

341
00:17:18,514 --> 00:17:19,544
(The 17 days will be filled with joy.)

342
00:17:20,884 --> 00:17:25,784
(Today, Ms. Kim greets her second day alone.)

343
00:17:30,824 --> 00:17:34,234
(But is she really alone?)

344
00:17:38,534 --> 00:17:40,874
(A moving camera)

345
00:17:42,774 --> 00:17:44,074
Did you sleep well?

346
00:17:47,344 --> 00:17:50,144
(Another encounter)

347
00:17:56,984 --> 00:17:58,584
The resolution is bad, right?

348
00:17:59,254 --> 00:18:01,224
(Shaking)

349
00:18:01,794 --> 00:18:02,824
Is it good?

350
00:18:03,154 --> 00:18:04,994
(Nodding)

351
00:18:06,894 --> 00:18:10,094
(Leaving because she's bare-faced)

352
00:18:12,804 --> 00:18:16,234
(Ms. Kim is washing up.)

353
00:18:17,174 --> 00:18:19,874
(Get ready with Tae Ri.)

354
00:18:21,014 --> 00:18:23,914
(1. Wash face with skincare products.)

355
00:18:24,544 --> 00:18:27,384
(Her hair is unmanageable.)

356
00:18:28,684 --> 00:18:30,923
(2. Leave the bears...)

357
00:18:30,924 --> 00:18:33,484
(to take care of the hair in the way.)

358
00:18:34,994 --> 00:18:37,694
(3. Apply cream.)

359
00:18:38,524 --> 00:18:40,664
(Patting)

360
00:18:41,994 --> 00:18:44,704
(Applying it thoroughly down to her neck)

361
00:18:46,104 --> 00:18:48,803
(4. Next, cushion foundation)

362
00:18:48,804 --> 00:18:51,104
(Apply it evenly.)

363
00:18:53,504 --> 00:18:56,244
(5. Apply some hair products.)

364
00:18:57,214 --> 00:19:00,344
(Her everyday makeup is done.)

365
00:19:00,854 --> 00:19:01,884
Okay.

366
00:19:02,654 --> 00:19:03,714
And...

367
00:19:07,994 --> 00:19:12,124
(She goes over the class one last time.)

368
00:19:17,904 --> 00:19:19,163
What could I do for the one-man play?

369
00:19:19,164 --> 00:19:20,563
(1st period: Short introductions between teacher and students)

370
00:19:20,564 --> 00:19:21,734
Just go on stage.

371
00:19:22,604 --> 00:19:23,904
Just go on stage and...

372
00:19:24,004 --> 00:19:26,544
(A 1-man play?)

373
00:19:28,374 --> 00:19:31,444
(Yesterday at the acting classroom)

374
00:19:33,314 --> 00:19:35,454
Little did I imagine we'd have a stage.

375
00:19:36,614 --> 00:19:39,924
(She spotted the stage when touring the classroom for the first time.)

376
00:19:41,854 --> 00:19:42,924
Does it work?

377
00:19:45,694 --> 00:19:47,564
(Thinking)

378
00:19:49,264 --> 00:19:52,334
To explain theater,

379
00:19:52,834 --> 00:19:54,234
I thought it'd be a good idea.

380
00:19:54,404 --> 00:19:57,233
I'd be on stage.

381
00:19:57,234 --> 00:19:58,403
(The stage gave her an idea for the first class.)

382
00:19:58,404 --> 00:20:00,244
If I act something out...

383
00:20:00,844 --> 00:20:03,873
while the students are sitting in the so-called seats.

384
00:20:03,874 --> 00:20:05,684
(A 1-man play to introduce herself and acting)

385
00:20:06,714 --> 00:20:08,914
Show them what a performance is.

386
00:20:10,354 --> 00:20:12,184
I'd need a script.

387
00:20:15,694 --> 00:20:20,264
(There is no script ready 4 hours before the class.)

388
00:20:22,564 --> 00:20:24,804
Coffee.

389
00:20:30,074 --> 00:20:32,003
(Screaming)

390
00:20:32,004 --> 00:20:33,304
Did they go to school?

391
00:20:34,214 --> 00:20:35,214
No way.

392
00:20:36,744 --> 00:20:39,084
(Telescope)

393
00:20:40,784 --> 00:20:42,814
I should have brought a better one.

394
00:20:43,114 --> 00:20:45,283
If I had known the house was so far away.,

395
00:20:45,284 --> 00:20:46,553
(Tae Ri is a birdwatcher.)

396
00:20:46,554 --> 00:20:47,654
I would have brought it.

397
00:20:50,094 --> 00:20:52,994
(Spying the school)

398
00:20:54,464 --> 00:20:55,464
Wait.

399
00:20:56,134 --> 00:20:58,234
(She spots something.)

400
00:20:59,504 --> 00:21:03,004
(She sees children beyond the fence.)

401
00:21:07,774 --> 00:21:09,514
Seeing the children,

402
00:21:10,214 --> 00:21:12,444
I suddenly got scared.

403
00:21:14,384 --> 00:21:16,554
That I had to give a class.

404
00:21:18,054 --> 00:21:20,254
And that today was the day.

405
00:21:23,124 --> 00:21:24,154
Also,

406
00:21:25,094 --> 00:21:28,494
that I didn't feel ready enough.

407
00:21:30,494 --> 00:21:33,034
I wish someone would tell me this is a dream.

408
00:21:39,274 --> 00:21:40,604
I'm all alone right now,

409
00:21:41,474 --> 00:21:43,074
and I have to meet those kids soon?

410
00:21:48,384 --> 00:21:51,723
(Reality finally sets in, and she's overwhelmed.)

411
00:21:51,724 --> 00:21:55,094
I suddenly had a realization.

412
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,694
No!

413
00:22:04,934 --> 00:22:06,364
Ms. Kim!

414
00:22:06,664 --> 00:22:08,134
Ms. Kim!

415
00:22:09,374 --> 00:22:11,703
Ms. Kim! Ms. Kim?

416
00:22:11,704 --> 00:22:15,944
(The weight of being a teacher suddenly hits her.)

417
00:22:24,214 --> 00:22:25,654
I'm so weak.

418
00:22:31,064 --> 00:22:37,364
(She tries to pull herself together against this vague fear.)

419
00:22:37,664 --> 00:22:38,764
Gosh.

420
00:22:46,304 --> 00:22:52,584
(But she eventually succumbs to the pressure.)

421
00:22:54,214 --> 00:22:55,913
How do I get rid of this fear?

422
00:22:55,914 --> 00:22:57,484
I'm so afraid.

423
00:23:09,464 --> 00:23:11,304
Shoot, this is driving me insane.

424
00:23:21,774 --> 00:23:24,114
Anxiety suddenly grew,

425
00:23:24,684 --> 00:23:26,514
and it felt complicated.

426
00:23:27,644 --> 00:23:29,284
I couldn't stop crying.

427
00:23:33,884 --> 00:23:36,623
This is my first time ever being a teacher.

428
00:23:36,624 --> 00:23:39,924
(She's becoming a teacher for the first time in her life.)

429
00:23:55,944 --> 00:24:01,853
(She sits still and looks out the window.)

430
00:24:01,854 --> 00:24:05,024
(And something occurs to her.)

431
00:24:19,364 --> 00:24:23,834
(I love mountains and spacing out.)

432
00:24:27,044 --> 00:24:28,873
(I also love driving!)

433
00:24:28,874 --> 00:24:31,913
(I'm currently doing something...)

434
00:24:31,914 --> 00:24:35,883
(for the first time...)

435
00:24:35,884 --> 00:24:39,623
(in my life!)

436
00:24:39,624 --> 00:24:45,464
(She starts by introducing herself.)

437
00:24:47,864 --> 00:24:50,093
(Today, I came...)

438
00:24:50,094 --> 00:24:55,104
(to Yongheung Elementary School to meet my first students!)

439
00:25:00,604 --> 00:25:08,013
(The weight of responsibility before her eyes...)

440
00:25:08,014 --> 00:25:12,124
(gradually turned into excitement.)

441
00:25:12,584 --> 00:25:18,364
(I'll be meeting you soon.)

442
00:25:21,094 --> 00:25:24,904
(She fills every line with her utmost sincerity.)

443
00:25:25,734 --> 00:25:28,703
It's too long! How are you going to memorize this?

444
00:25:28,704 --> 00:25:30,103
(I'm Ms. Kim, and I'll be teaching your after-school acting class.)

445
00:25:30,104 --> 00:25:33,304
(Her sincerity ended up too lengthy.)

446
00:25:35,014 --> 00:25:36,014
Easier...

447
00:25:37,914 --> 00:25:39,214
Hi!

448
00:25:39,514 --> 00:25:42,313
The seats are all filled!

449
00:25:42,314 --> 00:25:43,314
(She starts practicing out loud.)

450
00:25:43,414 --> 00:25:45,524
Are you all here to see me today?

451
00:25:47,254 --> 00:25:49,194
Let me introduce myself.

452
00:25:50,254 --> 00:25:53,164
I love mountains...

453
00:25:53,794 --> 00:25:55,594
and spacing out.

454
00:25:55,964 --> 00:25:57,964
And I love sleeping.

455
00:25:58,164 --> 00:26:00,433
Oh, I also love driving.

456
00:26:00,434 --> 00:26:03,934
I love drinking coffee and eating apples.

457
00:26:04,334 --> 00:26:08,174
And today, I'm at Yongheung Elementary School...

458
00:26:08,374 --> 00:26:11,184
to meet my first-ever students.

459
00:26:11,384 --> 00:26:13,584
When I close and open my eyes,

460
00:26:13,684 --> 00:26:15,114
they'll be right here.

461
00:26:16,654 --> 00:26:17,684
Pop!

462
00:26:18,454 --> 00:26:21,954
Hi, everyone! Thanks for coming.

463
00:26:22,594 --> 00:26:25,793
I'll be teaching an after-school acting class,

464
00:26:25,794 --> 00:26:27,324
and I'm Ms. Kim Tae Ri.

465
00:26:30,764 --> 00:26:34,364
(Actually, she's not so sure about this.)

466
00:26:35,874 --> 00:26:38,774
It's okay. Take your time. It's okay to make mistakes.

467
00:26:39,944 --> 00:26:41,004
It's okay.

468
00:26:44,244 --> 00:26:45,284
And then...

469
00:26:46,044 --> 00:26:49,653
Now, I'd like to talk about what theater is...

470
00:26:49,654 --> 00:26:50,884
with you guys.

471
00:26:51,824 --> 00:26:53,754
What do you think theater is?

472
00:26:56,954 --> 00:26:59,894
I first acted...

473
00:26:59,994 --> 00:27:01,964
in college.

474
00:27:04,664 --> 00:27:05,664
Back then...

475
00:27:07,064 --> 00:27:09,173
The role I played was a girl...

476
00:27:09,174 --> 00:27:11,844
coming to Seoul and dreaming of becoming an actress.

477
00:27:12,874 --> 00:27:14,614
I played that role,

478
00:27:16,074 --> 00:27:17,544
the lights went dark,

479
00:27:18,984 --> 00:27:21,284
and the audience started clapping.

480
00:27:22,984 --> 00:27:24,854
That felt so good.

481
00:27:25,724 --> 00:27:29,123
It was a type of feeling...

482
00:27:29,124 --> 00:27:32,364
that I had never experienced before in my life.

483
00:27:32,464 --> 00:27:33,863
I thoroughly enjoyed it.

484
00:27:33,864 --> 00:27:37,933
That's when I realized...

485
00:27:37,934 --> 00:27:41,433
that I could make acting my life's work...

486
00:27:41,434 --> 00:27:43,674
and never grow tired of it.

487
00:27:43,774 --> 00:27:45,844
That's when I tried...

488
00:27:47,044 --> 00:27:49,213
to become an actor.

489
00:27:49,214 --> 00:27:50,843
(Tae Ri started acting through plays.)

490
00:27:50,844 --> 00:27:52,383
I got a manicure.

491
00:27:52,384 --> 00:27:56,614
(From a college theater club to the stages of Daehak-ro...)

492
00:27:58,484 --> 00:27:59,854
I know now.

493
00:28:01,394 --> 00:28:05,194
(And overcoming a 1,500-to-1 competition for "The Handmaiden...")

494
00:28:10,794 --> 00:28:12,634
Kim Tae Ri from "The Handmaiden."

495
00:28:13,164 --> 00:28:14,434
Congratulations.

496
00:28:14,634 --> 00:28:16,074
Kim Tae Ri from "Revenant."

497
00:28:16,374 --> 00:28:17,404
Congratulations.

498
00:28:17,874 --> 00:28:19,244
The Top Excellence Award goes to...

499
00:28:19,344 --> 00:28:20,773
Kim Tae Ri from "Jeongnyeon: The Star Is Born."

500
00:28:20,774 --> 00:28:21,814
Congratulations.

501
00:28:22,874 --> 00:28:25,983
(Her every step...)

502
00:28:25,984 --> 00:28:29,414
(has shaped the actor she is today.)

503
00:28:31,184 --> 00:28:33,123
(Starting theater,)

504
00:28:33,124 --> 00:28:35,693
(playing Sook Hee in "The Handmaiden,")

505
00:28:35,694 --> 00:28:40,194
(and winning this award were all a coincidence.)

506
00:28:41,024 --> 00:28:45,163
(I am deeply grateful to everyone I've met...)

507
00:28:45,164 --> 00:28:48,804
(through the many strokes of luck and coincidences.)

508
00:28:49,304 --> 00:28:50,533
I've always thought,

509
00:28:50,534 --> 00:28:53,043
"What if I had experienced this a little bit sooner,"

510
00:28:53,044 --> 00:28:55,014
"in high school, in middle school,"

511
00:28:55,114 --> 00:28:58,544
"or even in elementary school?"

512
00:28:58,644 --> 00:29:00,984
"How different would I be today?"

513
00:29:01,084 --> 00:29:03,583
"My whole world would be different by now."

514
00:29:03,584 --> 00:29:06,383
I had thought of that a lot.

515
00:29:06,384 --> 00:29:09,753
So, I thought it'd be good to give the youth...

516
00:29:09,754 --> 00:29:10,854
a chance to learn acting.

517
00:29:11,194 --> 00:29:15,293
That thought has always been in the back of my head.

518
00:29:15,294 --> 00:29:17,594
So, in that sense...

519
00:29:19,464 --> 00:29:20,764
But the problem is...

520
00:29:22,104 --> 00:29:23,604
that the only thing...

521
00:29:24,034 --> 00:29:27,704
I'm good at is acting.

522
00:29:27,874 --> 00:29:30,244
Being a teacher...

523
00:29:30,814 --> 00:29:34,214
(It's her first time being a teacher.)

524
00:29:34,314 --> 00:29:35,754
Being a teacher is so hard.

525
00:29:36,684 --> 00:29:38,523
(She's on the verge of a new beginning.)

526
00:29:38,524 --> 00:29:41,454
I've already interviewed...

527
00:29:41,894 --> 00:29:44,524
some of the senior actors by myself.

528
00:29:45,464 --> 00:29:47,424
When I talked to Moon So Ri,

529
00:29:47,794 --> 00:29:50,663
she told me about Lee Sang Woo,

530
00:29:50,664 --> 00:29:52,663
a director she had often worked with.

531
00:29:52,664 --> 00:29:54,663
Yesterday, I talked to Yeom Hye Ran.

532
00:29:54,664 --> 00:29:59,203
She thought that acting was a foundation for everything.

533
00:29:59,204 --> 00:30:01,714
That's what she told me.

534
00:30:02,144 --> 00:30:05,414
People who had experience in teaching other people,

535
00:30:05,784 --> 00:30:07,784
people who had experience in producing works...

536
00:30:08,384 --> 00:30:09,713
I've interviewed those people.

537
00:30:09,714 --> 00:30:10,954
(She incessantly collected experiences.)

538
00:30:11,184 --> 00:30:14,223
Even yesterday, I was texting with Sun Kyu.

539
00:30:14,224 --> 00:30:15,294
Actor Jin Sun Kyu.

540
00:30:15,724 --> 00:30:17,123
He said that he had taught a class 15 years ago.

541
00:30:17,124 --> 00:30:20,823
So, I said, "Okay, I must interview you."

542
00:30:20,824 --> 00:30:21,834
(He wins an interview.)

543
00:30:21,864 --> 00:30:23,334
But I heard you were really busy.

544
00:30:23,764 --> 00:30:24,964
I've been so busy.

545
00:30:26,034 --> 00:30:29,033
I talked to the choreographer for "Jeongnyeon: The Star Is Born,"

546
00:30:29,034 --> 00:30:31,774
so I could learn from her.

547
00:30:33,044 --> 00:30:36,144
(She taught her the warmup dance routine.)

548
00:30:36,644 --> 00:30:39,014
(Tae Ri uses the same-side arm and leg.)

549
00:30:48,524 --> 00:30:51,524
(She failed to learn.)

550
00:30:52,864 --> 00:30:55,994
I was clumsy, so I struggled since it was my first time.

551
00:30:58,534 --> 00:31:00,064
What if I open my eyes and burst into tears?

552
00:31:00,864 --> 00:31:01,973
I feel like I will.

553
00:31:01,974 --> 00:31:03,534
(She's anxious and worried as it's her first time.)

554
00:31:03,874 --> 00:31:05,974
But I'm a teacher now,

555
00:31:06,244 --> 00:31:09,074
so I must prepare myself to live up to the position.

556
00:31:09,514 --> 00:31:12,213
You're doing great, Tae Ri. You're the best.

557
00:31:12,214 --> 00:31:13,784
(She gave it her all.)

558
00:31:14,044 --> 00:31:15,084
You're doing great.

559
00:31:16,814 --> 00:31:17,884
All done?

560
00:31:19,354 --> 00:31:20,524
Is everything perfect?

561
00:31:22,094 --> 00:31:24,494
Good. I'm going to work.

562
00:31:24,924 --> 00:31:26,293
(She finally got everything ready.)

563
00:31:26,294 --> 00:31:29,533
I forgot to wear socks.

564
00:31:29,534 --> 00:31:31,904
(Except for her socks)

565
00:31:36,274 --> 00:31:37,434
I can do this.

566
00:31:39,544 --> 00:31:40,974
I can do it.

567
00:31:48,084 --> 00:31:51,924
(Ms. Kim goes to work for the first time.)

568
00:31:53,124 --> 00:31:55,624
Help me out, room.

569
00:31:57,624 --> 00:31:58,723
It's 1:30pm.

570
00:31:58,724 --> 00:32:00,324
(She sets up for her class.)

571
00:32:00,594 --> 00:32:01,694
Kyung Mo.

572
00:32:03,164 --> 00:32:04,194
Eun Soo.

573
00:32:06,064 --> 00:32:09,904
Okay? One, two, three, four, five, six, seven. Seven name tags.

574
00:32:11,204 --> 00:32:13,643
(Next, she moves...)

575
00:32:13,644 --> 00:32:15,714
(boxes?)

576
00:32:16,044 --> 00:32:18,484
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven.

577
00:32:19,084 --> 00:32:20,483
The seats are ready.

578
00:32:20,484 --> 00:32:21,613
(Seats for her monologue are ready.)

579
00:32:21,614 --> 00:32:22,754
And then...

580
00:32:23,614 --> 00:32:25,354
(Next, she lifts a desk.)

581
00:32:29,954 --> 00:32:31,994
(Writing without hesitation)

582
00:32:38,064 --> 00:32:39,733
(The sign for her monologue is ready.)

583
00:32:39,734 --> 00:32:40,963
(Here is the seating! Pick any spot you like!)

584
00:32:40,964 --> 00:32:45,073
(The show is about to start! Please take your seats!)

585
00:32:45,074 --> 00:32:46,444
Perfect.

586
00:32:47,304 --> 00:32:50,713
(She's all ready for class.)

587
00:32:50,714 --> 00:32:54,044
(The children will arrive soon.)

588
00:32:57,784 --> 00:33:01,154
(This is the actual sound of her heartbeat.)

589
00:33:05,294 --> 00:33:10,234
(She warms up to find composure.)

590
00:33:18,034 --> 00:33:21,274
(The sound of the bell breaks her composure.)

591
00:33:26,684 --> 00:33:30,414
(A human being approaches while breathing heavily.)

592
00:33:33,124 --> 00:33:35,794
(She quickly hides.)

593
00:33:36,654 --> 00:33:38,594
(Wish me luck!)

594
00:33:49,104 --> 00:33:53,474
(She hopes to pull it off just as she practiced.)

595
00:34:04,884 --> 00:34:07,754
(Who's the first student to join the acting class?)

596
00:34:08,654 --> 00:34:10,854
(Jang Won Jin)

597
00:34:11,824 --> 00:34:13,694
(Amazed)

598
00:34:16,464 --> 00:34:18,464
Awesome!

599
00:34:19,104 --> 00:34:22,234
(She senses the cuteness beyond the curtain.)

600
00:34:25,544 --> 00:34:26,604
Hi.

601
00:34:30,574 --> 00:34:33,684
(He reads the sign and takes a seat.)

602
00:34:34,114 --> 00:34:36,384
Are we playing Find the Camera?

603
00:34:42,324 --> 00:34:44,453
One, two, three...

604
00:34:44,454 --> 00:34:45,664
It's the gym!

605
00:34:46,394 --> 00:34:48,364
- Long time no see.
- Come on.

606
00:34:48,864 --> 00:34:50,434
What's all this?

607
00:34:50,534 --> 00:34:52,363
They want you to sit wherever you want.

608
00:34:52,364 --> 00:34:53,434
It says it here.

609
00:34:54,804 --> 00:34:56,073
No way.

610
00:34:56,074 --> 00:34:57,274
"Pick any spot you like."

611
00:34:57,804 --> 00:34:58,804
Sit.

612
00:34:59,274 --> 00:35:01,003
(Amazed)

613
00:35:01,004 --> 00:35:02,774
- Let's sit together!
- Shush.

614
00:35:02,874 --> 00:35:04,673
- Let's sit together.
- Shush.

615
00:35:04,674 --> 00:35:05,744
Let's sit together.

616
00:35:05,914 --> 00:35:07,043
Let's sit together.

617
00:35:07,044 --> 00:35:08,244
So cute.

618
00:35:10,014 --> 00:35:12,254
So cute!

619
00:35:13,054 --> 00:35:14,654
Here we go. In 1, 2, 3.

620
00:35:15,294 --> 00:35:16,594
- What?
- What?

621
00:35:17,554 --> 00:35:18,724
It's all set up.

622
00:35:20,964 --> 00:35:22,094
What?

623
00:35:22,134 --> 00:35:23,534
What's all this?

624
00:35:25,334 --> 00:35:26,434
No way.

625
00:35:26,634 --> 00:35:27,733
What?

626
00:35:27,734 --> 00:35:29,704
It changed so much.

627
00:35:30,104 --> 00:35:32,173
(The gym they're used to...)

628
00:35:32,174 --> 00:35:33,603
(turned into an acting class.)

629
00:35:33,604 --> 00:35:35,243
They designed it so nicely.

630
00:35:35,244 --> 00:35:37,843
- It doesn't feel like the gym.
- It's not.

631
00:35:37,844 --> 00:35:39,043
It's a whole new place.

632
00:35:39,044 --> 00:35:42,184
The gym turned into a calming area.

633
00:35:42,754 --> 00:35:44,254
Holy moly!

634
00:35:44,614 --> 00:35:46,184
Where are our teachers?

635
00:35:46,624 --> 00:35:48,824
I know, right? I don't see any teachers.

636
00:35:49,924 --> 00:35:51,824
The teachers are...

637
00:35:52,364 --> 00:35:54,294
- Wait.
- What?

638
00:35:54,394 --> 00:35:56,133
- Wait.
- What?

639
00:35:56,134 --> 00:35:58,193
- What?
- What's going on?

640
00:35:58,194 --> 00:36:00,034
- There's something up there.
- No way.

641
00:36:00,104 --> 00:36:01,633
- What's happening?
- Let's watch.

642
00:36:01,634 --> 00:36:02,733
- What is it?
- What?

643
00:36:02,734 --> 00:36:03,833
- What's happening?
- Let's watch.

644
00:36:03,834 --> 00:36:05,274
(Peeking)

645
00:36:05,644 --> 00:36:07,044
- "Shush." - "Shush."

646
00:36:07,604 --> 00:36:09,243
- There's someone behind it.
- Be quiet.

647
00:36:09,244 --> 00:36:11,344
- Be quiet, guys.
- Okay.

648
00:36:13,984 --> 00:36:15,684
"The show will start now."

649
00:36:18,384 --> 00:36:22,794
(The 7 audiences are looking forward to it.)

650
00:36:28,534 --> 00:36:31,264
(Ta-da)

651
00:36:33,834 --> 00:36:37,574
(The kids meet Ms. Kim for the first time.)

652
00:36:39,374 --> 00:36:40,773
Wow.

653
00:36:40,774 --> 00:36:44,013
Once again, the audience filled...

654
00:36:44,014 --> 00:36:46,013
every single seat!

655
00:36:46,014 --> 00:36:47,813
It's so nice to meet you.

656
00:36:47,814 --> 00:36:49,013
Hi, guys!

657
00:36:49,014 --> 00:36:51,084
- Hello.
- Hello.

658
00:36:51,284 --> 00:36:53,623
Are you all here to see me?

659
00:36:53,624 --> 00:36:54,724
- Yes!
- Yes!

660
00:36:55,224 --> 00:36:57,524
Let me introduce myself.

661
00:36:58,524 --> 00:36:59,524
I...

662
00:37:01,524 --> 00:37:03,164
like mountains.

663
00:37:08,504 --> 00:37:10,374
I like sleeping.

664
00:37:10,434 --> 00:37:11,604
Snorlax.

665
00:37:15,444 --> 00:37:18,114
- Spacing out.
- And I like spacing out.

666
00:37:19,784 --> 00:37:21,313
- Honk, honk!
- Driving.

667
00:37:21,314 --> 00:37:24,414
- Driving.
- And I like driving. Also...

668
00:37:28,454 --> 00:37:31,093
- Soju?
- I like drinking coffee.

669
00:37:31,094 --> 00:37:32,124
Sorry.

670
00:37:34,794 --> 00:37:36,293
- Eating.
- It's food.

671
00:37:36,294 --> 00:37:38,333
And I love eating apples in the morning.

672
00:37:38,334 --> 00:37:39,404
Apples are tasty.

673
00:37:40,764 --> 00:37:41,764
Right!

674
00:37:42,274 --> 00:37:44,804
(Shushing)

675
00:37:46,174 --> 00:37:48,204
(Shush!)

676
00:37:49,144 --> 00:37:50,574
Today,

677
00:37:51,344 --> 00:37:54,283
I'm here to meet my first students.

678
00:37:54,284 --> 00:37:56,854
Right here at Yongheung Elementary School.

679
00:37:57,054 --> 00:38:00,483
- That's us.
- I'll be seeing them soon.

680
00:38:00,484 --> 00:38:03,054
I'm so nervous because it's my first time.

681
00:38:03,954 --> 00:38:05,364
When will I see them?

682
00:38:05,724 --> 00:38:10,694
When the light in the back goes out,

683
00:38:11,834 --> 00:38:15,234
and I close and open my eyes,

684
00:38:15,804 --> 00:38:18,234
my students will be sitting right before my eyes.

685
00:38:18,774 --> 00:38:20,304
Once I close my eyes,

686
00:38:20,604 --> 00:38:24,473
count "One, two, three" with me.

687
00:38:24,474 --> 00:38:25,584
- Yes!
- Okay?

688
00:38:26,784 --> 00:38:27,844
All right.

689
00:38:36,294 --> 00:38:40,324
- One, two, three!
- One, two, three!

690
00:38:41,564 --> 00:38:45,033
(Transforming)

691
00:38:45,034 --> 00:38:47,264
Hi, it's so nice to see you!

692
00:38:48,534 --> 00:38:50,104
Hi, everyone.

693
00:38:50,204 --> 00:38:51,373
(The monologue turns into a class.)

694
00:38:51,374 --> 00:38:52,973
Did you all enjoy the show?

695
00:38:52,974 --> 00:38:54,374
- Yes!
- Yes!

696
00:38:54,444 --> 00:38:57,213
I'll be teaching you acting...

697
00:38:57,214 --> 00:38:59,813
after school from now on.

698
00:38:59,814 --> 00:39:01,683
My name is Kim Tae Ri.

699
00:39:01,684 --> 00:39:02,853
Hi!

700
00:39:02,854 --> 00:39:03,983
Hi, Ms. Kim.

701
00:39:03,984 --> 00:39:07,184
(She greets them for the first time as a teacher.)

702
00:39:07,784 --> 00:39:12,924
Kids, what was on your mind when you came to this acting class?

703
00:39:13,864 --> 00:39:14,893
I thought it'd be fun.

704
00:39:14,894 --> 00:39:16,433
You thought it'd be fun.

705
00:39:16,434 --> 00:39:17,693
- Going on a picnic?
- It sounded fun.

706
00:39:17,694 --> 00:39:20,663
A picnic? It sounded fun to you?

707
00:39:20,664 --> 00:39:23,274
Yes, having fun is the most important part in acting.

708
00:39:23,534 --> 00:39:25,173
If it's fun, that's all that matters.

709
00:39:25,174 --> 00:39:27,303
I just came, thinking, "Tra-la-la."

710
00:39:27,304 --> 00:39:29,314
Yes, that's all you need.

711
00:39:29,744 --> 00:39:30,943
Tra-la-la.

712
00:39:30,944 --> 00:39:33,244
(Tra-la-la)

713
00:39:34,484 --> 00:39:37,084
It was their first time at acting class,

714
00:39:37,384 --> 00:39:40,123
so I believed I needed to explain to them...

715
00:39:40,124 --> 00:39:42,423
why we were gathered.

716
00:39:42,424 --> 00:39:45,364
Who has experience in acting?

717
00:39:46,264 --> 00:39:48,894
- I've only seen it on TV.
- No one?

718
00:39:49,634 --> 00:39:54,463
All right, kids. Can you tell me the elements of a play?

719
00:39:54,464 --> 00:39:55,504
Acting.

720
00:39:55,604 --> 00:39:57,773
- Yes, acting.
- Acting.

721
00:39:57,774 --> 00:39:59,473
- People.
- People?

722
00:39:59,474 --> 00:40:01,203
We need the audience. What else?

723
00:40:01,204 --> 00:40:04,473
- Clothes!
- Clothes? Yes, we need costumes.

724
00:40:04,474 --> 00:40:07,284
- Makeup.
- Yes, we need makeup.

725
00:40:07,344 --> 00:40:09,313
- The stage.
- The stage! That's right.

726
00:40:09,314 --> 00:40:11,513
The stage is crucial.

727
00:40:11,514 --> 00:40:13,523
Judging from your answers,

728
00:40:13,524 --> 00:40:16,824
you know a lot about theater.

729
00:40:17,354 --> 00:40:20,293
Do you know what we're doing on November 11?

730
00:40:20,294 --> 00:40:21,294
- The school arts festival.
- The school arts festival.

731
00:40:21,294 --> 00:40:22,294
The school arts festival!

732
00:40:22,295 --> 00:40:23,663
Don't tell me we'll be acting that day.

733
00:40:23,664 --> 00:40:25,403
At the school arts festival,

734
00:40:25,404 --> 00:40:27,634
- Are we acting?
- we'll perform a play.

735
00:40:28,204 --> 00:40:29,733
(Crying)

736
00:40:29,734 --> 00:40:30,773
No!

737
00:40:30,774 --> 00:40:33,474
That's the goal of this acting class!

738
00:40:33,504 --> 00:40:36,913
- Oh, my gosh!
- Oh, my gosh!

739
00:40:36,914 --> 00:40:39,714
Will you give me a more positive response?

740
00:40:41,014 --> 00:40:44,053
(With the kids who are acting for the first time,)

741
00:40:44,054 --> 00:40:47,383
(they warm up,)

742
00:40:47,384 --> 00:40:50,793
(read the script,)

743
00:40:50,794 --> 00:40:53,293
(and make music.)

744
00:40:53,294 --> 00:40:54,623
Good. That's perfect.

745
00:40:54,624 --> 00:40:56,394
Let's go and meet them!

746
00:40:56,934 --> 00:40:57,934
(The 10 colorful acting classes)

747
00:40:57,935 --> 00:41:01,203
Theater is a foundation for everything.

748
00:41:01,204 --> 00:41:03,574
You can imagine various things.

749
00:41:03,634 --> 00:41:05,074
Kids, you should be afraid.

750
00:41:05,674 --> 00:41:07,943
You get to express them.

751
00:41:07,944 --> 00:41:10,244
The lion flower has bloomed!

752
00:41:10,274 --> 00:41:11,913
(A good example)

753
00:41:11,914 --> 00:41:13,014
How...

754
00:41:13,114 --> 00:41:15,314
(When they don't do so well because it's their first time...)

755
00:41:15,884 --> 00:41:16,914
(You're the best actor right now.)

756
00:41:17,314 --> 00:41:19,224
(She bombards them with encouragement and compliments.)

757
00:41:19,354 --> 00:41:20,384
Confidence!

758
00:41:21,484 --> 00:41:23,594
(Their confidence will be boosted.)

759
00:41:24,394 --> 00:41:28,224
(Theater is a promise.)

760
00:41:29,934 --> 00:41:32,734
(Theater is an exchange.)

761
00:41:33,204 --> 00:41:36,134
Along the process, you can learn...

762
00:41:36,204 --> 00:41:38,774
respect and consideration.

763
00:41:38,944 --> 00:41:40,574
(Hi, I'm Anh Sung Jae.)

764
00:41:40,744 --> 00:41:42,973
And it's the joy of creating.

765
00:41:42,974 --> 00:41:43,974
(Theater is the joy of creating with a variety of people.)

766
00:41:43,975 --> 00:41:45,274
That's what theater is.

767
00:41:47,144 --> 00:41:48,144
(To perform at the school arts festival)

768
00:41:48,145 --> 00:41:50,913
I hope they share the feeling...

769
00:41:50,914 --> 00:41:53,083
of creating something together.

770
00:41:53,084 --> 00:41:54,184
We are...

771
00:41:54,724 --> 00:41:56,524
(We are one!)

772
00:41:56,654 --> 00:41:58,754
(We can do it!)

773
00:41:58,964 --> 00:42:00,124
(Yes!)

774
00:42:00,524 --> 00:42:01,993
(Let's go!)

775
00:42:01,994 --> 00:42:04,294
- We can do this!
- In 1, 2, 3.

776
00:42:06,134 --> 00:42:08,564
Defeat the villain!

777
00:42:11,574 --> 00:42:14,004
Do you think you'll keep acting...

778
00:42:14,404 --> 00:42:16,073
after this play?

779
00:42:16,074 --> 00:42:17,074
- Yes!
- Yes!

780
00:42:17,974 --> 00:42:19,943
Hyo Min, will you come to acting class if we open another one?

781
00:42:19,944 --> 00:42:20,984
Yes.

782
00:42:21,514 --> 00:42:22,754
- You will?
- Yes.

783
00:42:23,084 --> 00:42:24,153
- Is it fun?
- Yes.

784
00:42:24,154 --> 00:42:26,023
- Give me the camera.
- That makes me so happy.

785
00:42:26,024 --> 00:42:28,583
All right, then. Let's film three more.

786
00:42:28,584 --> 00:42:32,763
I felt proud because I could do it from start to finish.

787
00:42:32,764 --> 00:42:34,363
I want to be in another acting class...

788
00:42:34,364 --> 00:42:36,364
because the teachers were amazing.

789
00:42:36,534 --> 00:42:38,904
I want to be in acting class again.

790
00:42:39,704 --> 00:42:42,674
- We'll never forget you!
- We'll never forget you!

791
00:42:45,104 --> 00:42:47,844
What if Yongheung Elementary has a bunch of newcomers?

792
00:42:48,144 --> 00:42:49,814
- That'd be so nice.
- Yes.

793
00:42:51,174 --> 00:42:54,214
Because it's the only school in the area with an acting class?

794
00:42:54,314 --> 00:42:56,054
Yes. To perform plays.

795
00:42:59,124 --> 00:43:01,884
I hope we don't just exist in this fleeting moment,

796
00:43:04,594 --> 00:43:06,964
but stay with them for a long time.

797
00:43:08,824 --> 00:43:11,434
(For Yongheung Elementary School and its acting class to continue,)

798
00:43:12,404 --> 00:43:15,264
(today's first class will begin.)

799
00:43:15,874 --> 00:43:19,944
It's their first time experiencing what it's like to be in a play.

800
00:43:20,844 --> 00:43:22,774
I want them to feel comfortable.

801
00:43:23,674 --> 00:43:25,584
You have to find it fun first.

802
00:43:27,384 --> 00:43:30,513
(First class: First greeting)

803
00:43:30,514 --> 00:43:34,554
(Lesson 1: Introduction to Theater)

804
00:43:35,624 --> 00:43:38,094
Now, we're going to start introducing ourselves.

805
00:43:38,454 --> 00:43:39,464
"I like..."

806
00:43:40,694 --> 00:43:44,433
"doing this, and my name is this."

807
00:43:44,434 --> 00:43:46,063
- That's the format.
- Okay.

808
00:43:46,064 --> 00:43:47,534
I'll show you first.

809
00:43:48,164 --> 00:43:49,204
I like...

810
00:43:51,274 --> 00:43:52,503
- Gaming.
- Gaming?

811
00:43:52,504 --> 00:43:55,814
playing computer games, and my name is Kim Tae Ri.

812
00:43:56,244 --> 00:43:57,413
That's how you do it.

813
00:43:57,414 --> 00:43:58,813
But the rest of you...

814
00:43:58,814 --> 00:44:01,843
will repeat after the person.

815
00:44:01,844 --> 00:44:03,154
- Okay?
- Okay.

816
00:44:03,714 --> 00:44:05,483
Acting is...

817
00:44:05,484 --> 00:44:09,253
expressing with your mouth and body.

818
00:44:09,254 --> 00:44:10,723
(Acting is basically expressing yourself.)

819
00:44:10,724 --> 00:44:12,893
I think there should be lots of activities...

820
00:44:12,894 --> 00:44:15,564
in which you can express yourself as if you're playing.

821
00:44:15,864 --> 00:44:17,494
Who wants to volunteer?

822
00:44:17,794 --> 00:44:20,234
- What does that mean?
- Who wants to go first?

823
00:44:21,404 --> 00:44:22,534
Kyung Mo!

824
00:44:22,774 --> 00:44:24,733
- I'll go next!
- Listen to what Kyung Mo says...

825
00:44:24,734 --> 00:44:26,004
and repeat after him.

826
00:44:26,244 --> 00:44:27,244
Start.

827
00:44:27,245 --> 00:44:29,874
I like pull-up bars.

828
00:44:30,144 --> 00:44:32,643
You like pull-up bars.

829
00:44:32,644 --> 00:44:34,944
And I like playing mobile games.

830
00:44:35,854 --> 00:44:36,983
- Repeat after him.
- I am...

831
00:44:36,984 --> 00:44:38,414
a monkey.

832
00:44:38,754 --> 00:44:40,123
- A monkey?
- A monkey?

833
00:44:40,124 --> 00:44:41,424
That's a lot.

834
00:44:42,024 --> 00:44:44,024
Can you show us the pull-up bar again?

835
00:44:44,754 --> 00:44:47,194
- Try it, guys.
- Okay.

836
00:44:47,864 --> 00:44:49,763
There you go.

837
00:44:49,764 --> 00:44:51,333
Pull-up bars. What was next?

838
00:44:51,334 --> 00:44:53,063
- Mobile games!
- Mobile games.

839
00:44:53,064 --> 00:44:54,803
- How did he do it?
- Ding, ding.

840
00:44:54,804 --> 00:44:55,804
(Humming)

841
00:44:56,304 --> 00:44:58,203
(They seem experienced.)

842
00:44:58,204 --> 00:44:59,303
Well done!

843
00:44:59,304 --> 00:45:00,973
Nice to meet you, Kyung Mo!

844
00:45:00,974 --> 00:45:02,474
Thank you for introducing yourself.

845
00:45:02,844 --> 00:45:04,274
Next, Hyo Min.

846
00:45:04,774 --> 00:45:07,583
I like cats.

847
00:45:07,584 --> 00:45:08,584
Cats.

848
00:45:08,585 --> 00:45:11,313
Hyo Min, how did I describe it when I said...

849
00:45:11,314 --> 00:45:12,423
I liked the mountains?

850
00:45:12,424 --> 00:45:13,724
- Cats.
- Cats.

851
00:45:14,784 --> 00:45:16,453
This is a cat?

852
00:45:16,454 --> 00:45:18,153
- It is a cat!
- Cats.

853
00:45:18,154 --> 00:45:19,263
It is.

854
00:45:19,264 --> 00:45:20,993
Cats.

855
00:45:20,994 --> 00:45:22,534
- Next.
- I like...

856
00:45:22,764 --> 00:45:26,403
baseball, and my name is Cho Ha Yun.

857
00:45:26,404 --> 00:45:27,763
He likes baseball, guys!

858
00:45:27,764 --> 00:45:29,033
Try it.

859
00:45:29,034 --> 00:45:30,303
(Let's repeat after him.)

860
00:45:30,304 --> 00:45:32,133
I like swimming,

861
00:45:32,134 --> 00:45:33,373
and my name is Lee Ju Eun.

862
00:45:33,374 --> 00:45:34,544
How do you swim?

863
00:45:34,904 --> 00:45:36,013
(Breaststroke and freestyle)

864
00:45:36,014 --> 00:45:38,543
"I like swimming, and my name is Lee Ju Eun."

865
00:45:38,544 --> 00:45:40,214
(Splish-splash)

866
00:45:40,744 --> 00:45:43,984
I like drawing, and my name is Lee Eun Soo.

867
00:45:44,414 --> 00:45:45,754
You must draw on a tablet.

868
00:45:46,754 --> 00:45:50,223
I like cars, and my name is Jang Won Jin.

869
00:45:50,224 --> 00:45:52,094
Cars!

870
00:45:52,794 --> 00:45:54,263
(Vroom)

871
00:45:54,264 --> 00:45:58,234
I like baseball, and my name is Kim Do Hyun.

872
00:45:58,834 --> 00:46:00,564
- He's a batter.
- I want to be the batter!

873
00:46:01,334 --> 00:46:05,403
Now, I want to try it with food.

874
00:46:05,404 --> 00:46:07,604
You're not going to copy it. This time, you'll guess it.

875
00:46:08,344 --> 00:46:10,073
What is it? A battered meatball?

876
00:46:10,074 --> 00:46:11,144
- A steamed bun?
- An egg?

877
00:46:11,314 --> 00:46:12,543
- An egg?
- An egg?

878
00:46:12,544 --> 00:46:14,213
- Hotteok.
- It's a fruit.

879
00:46:14,214 --> 00:46:15,283
We got a hint.

880
00:46:15,284 --> 00:46:17,313
- Watermelon!
- Tangerine!

881
00:46:17,314 --> 00:46:18,484
What was it called?

882
00:46:18,954 --> 00:46:20,024
- What is it?
- Tangerine?

883
00:46:20,324 --> 00:46:21,623
Correct!

884
00:46:21,624 --> 00:46:23,324
(Correct!)

885
00:46:23,424 --> 00:46:25,324
Go ahead, Ju Eun. Start.

886
00:46:25,864 --> 00:46:26,993
Ice cream!

887
00:46:26,994 --> 00:46:28,894
(Ju Eun describes a type of food.)

888
00:46:30,894 --> 00:46:32,293
Legend!

889
00:46:32,294 --> 00:46:34,563
That was fast. It took him half a second.

890
00:46:34,564 --> 00:46:35,634
Next, Do Hyun.

891
00:46:36,304 --> 00:46:37,374
Jjamppong.

892
00:46:37,934 --> 00:46:39,774
- You poured soup.
- Jjajangmyeon!

893
00:46:39,974 --> 00:46:41,443
- Is it Buldak Ramen?
- Ramyeon.

894
00:46:41,444 --> 00:46:42,513
- Buldak Ramen?
- Correct.

895
00:46:42,514 --> 00:46:44,043
(Ju Eun got it right.)

896
00:46:44,044 --> 00:46:45,943
- It was Buldak?
- I love it.

897
00:46:45,944 --> 00:46:47,844
I guessed it from the way you added the sauce.

898
00:46:48,884 --> 00:46:50,983
- Wasn't it fun, guys?
- Yes!

899
00:46:50,984 --> 00:46:52,113
We guessed food.

900
00:46:52,114 --> 00:46:55,353
Theater is as simple as expressing...

901
00:46:55,354 --> 00:46:57,923
what's on your mind...

902
00:46:57,924 --> 00:46:59,463
with your body and words.

903
00:46:59,464 --> 00:47:00,824
- Was it fun?
- Yes.

904
00:47:01,394 --> 00:47:03,493
Before we move on to the next activity,

905
00:47:03,494 --> 00:47:06,134
I brought seven notebooks.

906
00:47:06,504 --> 00:47:09,634
These are question notes.

907
00:47:09,774 --> 00:47:11,874
When you have questions during class...

908
00:47:19,384 --> 00:47:21,184
- What?
- Recess?

909
00:47:21,514 --> 00:47:22,753
It's a recess.

910
00:47:22,754 --> 00:47:24,054
Kids.

911
00:47:24,154 --> 00:47:27,354
(Let's play!)

912
00:47:28,124 --> 00:47:29,654
(Stampeding)

913
00:47:31,124 --> 00:47:32,864
Ju Eun, let's go inside together.

914
00:47:35,224 --> 00:47:37,264
I love it! It's so cozy.

915
00:47:37,834 --> 00:47:39,094
I hope I have this at home.

916
00:47:39,764 --> 00:47:40,834
Hi!

917
00:47:42,204 --> 00:47:44,074
(Unlike the children who are excited,)

918
00:47:45,104 --> 00:47:46,873
(Ms. Kim shakes.)

919
00:47:46,874 --> 00:47:48,404
I hadn't looked at the clock once.

920
00:47:49,314 --> 00:47:50,674
I was dazed.

921
00:47:51,414 --> 00:47:52,414
I just...

922
00:47:52,844 --> 00:47:54,784
couldn't grasp the situation.

923
00:47:55,044 --> 00:47:57,514
My mind was blank.

924
00:47:59,854 --> 00:48:00,984
(Sighing deeply)

925
00:48:02,854 --> 00:48:05,494
(She takes a moment for herself.)

926
00:48:05,624 --> 00:48:07,093
We have to do Make a Promise.

927
00:48:07,094 --> 00:48:09,263
We won't have time for games, then.

928
00:48:09,264 --> 00:48:10,663
(Lesson 1)

929
00:48:10,664 --> 00:48:12,093
And Share Impressions.

930
00:48:12,094 --> 00:48:13,863
(She's not even halfway there.)

931
00:48:13,864 --> 00:48:15,234
I should speed things up.

932
00:48:17,204 --> 00:48:19,673
(The 2nd period begins.)

933
00:48:19,674 --> 00:48:20,774
Kids!

934
00:48:21,474 --> 00:48:24,114
What do you think we'll do next?

935
00:48:25,474 --> 00:48:28,243
We're going to play games.

936
00:48:28,244 --> 00:48:29,384
It should be fun.

937
00:48:29,954 --> 00:48:33,853
Start!

938
00:48:33,854 --> 00:48:35,754
(The game starts.)

939
00:48:38,054 --> 00:48:39,294
The purpose is...

940
00:48:39,624 --> 00:48:41,923
to help them find theater fun.

941
00:48:41,924 --> 00:48:43,963
(Play-based practice, creating a class everyone wants to join)

942
00:48:43,964 --> 00:48:48,604
I don't think there's any kid who doesn't like games.

943
00:48:50,174 --> 00:48:52,703
(Even the teacher likes it.)

944
00:48:52,704 --> 00:48:54,843
I'm still after you!

945
00:48:54,844 --> 00:48:57,143
(Building joyful experiences with theater...)

946
00:48:57,144 --> 00:48:58,943
(through games)

947
00:48:58,944 --> 00:49:01,984
The next game is...

948
00:49:02,684 --> 00:49:04,613
called Captain Monkey.

949
00:49:04,614 --> 00:49:05,783
- Captain Monkey.
- Captain Monkey.

950
00:49:05,784 --> 00:49:06,983
Captain Monkey.

951
00:49:06,984 --> 00:49:09,224
- Do we guess who the captain is?
- That's right.

952
00:49:09,294 --> 00:49:12,724
You copy the movements of Captain Monkey.

953
00:49:13,194 --> 00:49:16,194
We don't want to give it away to "it,"

954
00:49:16,594 --> 00:49:18,934
so "it" must observe and find out...

955
00:49:19,364 --> 00:49:21,864
who does the movements first. Okay?

956
00:49:22,264 --> 00:49:23,374
Can I open my eyes now?

957
00:49:23,534 --> 00:49:25,774
Open your eyes!

958
00:49:26,304 --> 00:49:29,143
Naturally, they have to observe other people...

959
00:49:29,144 --> 00:49:30,873
and try to understand them.

960
00:49:30,874 --> 00:49:32,713
I was hoping they'd be able...

961
00:49:32,714 --> 00:49:34,144
- to learn that.
- Why are you all looking at me?

962
00:49:35,044 --> 00:49:37,414
(Ju Eun is Captain Monkey.)

963
00:49:38,054 --> 00:49:39,753
(She changes the movements, watching Ju Eun.)

964
00:49:39,754 --> 00:49:40,784
Stop it.

965
00:49:41,224 --> 00:49:42,654
- Him.
- Wrong!

966
00:49:42,754 --> 00:49:45,254
- Wrong?
- "It" gets three chances.

967
00:49:46,364 --> 00:49:48,864
(While "it" turns his back on her...)

968
00:49:49,464 --> 00:49:51,134
(He missed it.)

969
00:49:51,964 --> 00:49:53,263
(There's a difficulty in his investigation.)

970
00:49:53,264 --> 00:49:54,363
(Having fun)

971
00:49:54,364 --> 00:49:56,873
I think you should guess it now.

972
00:49:56,874 --> 00:49:58,304
(Reading his face)

973
00:50:03,274 --> 00:50:04,843
(She got caught.)

974
00:50:04,844 --> 00:50:06,084
Oh, no.

975
00:50:06,284 --> 00:50:09,244
That was close. He saw you the moment you switched.

976
00:50:09,354 --> 00:50:10,914
That was so much fun.

977
00:50:11,584 --> 00:50:13,984
Should we come up with some class rules?

978
00:50:14,084 --> 00:50:16,254
- Yes.
- "Listen to the teacher."

979
00:50:17,424 --> 00:50:18,654
Thank you for that.

980
00:50:19,224 --> 00:50:20,493
- What?
- No lying down.

981
00:50:20,494 --> 00:50:21,893
No screaming.

982
00:50:21,894 --> 00:50:24,594
- No fighting?
- That's a good one.

983
00:50:25,064 --> 00:50:26,504
Foundations of theater...

984
00:50:26,964 --> 00:50:29,374
are respect and promise.

985
00:50:29,874 --> 00:50:32,974
Theater itself is like a promise.

986
00:50:33,244 --> 00:50:35,303
That's respect for each other.

987
00:50:35,304 --> 00:50:39,013
They are something crucial...

988
00:50:39,014 --> 00:50:40,784
to the making of our play.

989
00:50:41,444 --> 00:50:44,253
It's time for your question notes.

990
00:50:44,254 --> 00:50:46,423
If you missed the timing to ask me a question,

991
00:50:46,424 --> 00:50:48,053
or if you were too shy...

992
00:50:48,054 --> 00:50:49,993
to ask publicly,

993
00:50:49,994 --> 00:50:52,594
you can write them down.

994
00:50:53,094 --> 00:50:55,894
I'll write my responses and return these to you.

995
00:50:56,294 --> 00:50:58,893
Can we ask anything we want?

996
00:50:58,894 --> 00:51:00,134
Of course.

997
00:51:00,334 --> 00:51:01,603
What we couldn't ask.

998
00:51:01,604 --> 00:51:03,403
While preparing for this show,

999
00:51:03,404 --> 00:51:05,034
I met several people...

1000
00:51:05,474 --> 00:51:07,204
who all told me...

1001
00:51:07,404 --> 00:51:10,344
that I should listen. I should listen to the children.

1002
00:51:11,014 --> 00:51:14,683
All right! Let's take some time to share how we felt.

1003
00:51:14,684 --> 00:51:17,113
Let's all share...

1004
00:51:17,114 --> 00:51:18,914
how today was for you.

1005
00:51:19,254 --> 00:51:21,424
Kyung Mo, how was the class?

1006
00:51:21,524 --> 00:51:24,593
Me? My excitement was as big as the Milky Way.

1007
00:51:24,594 --> 00:51:26,394
As big as the Milky Way?

1008
00:51:26,894 --> 00:51:30,534
And? Was it just as fun as you expected?

1009
00:51:30,834 --> 00:51:33,663
- Was it as fun as the Milky Way?
- Yes, it was so much fun.

1010
00:51:33,664 --> 00:51:34,964
I'm so happy.

1011
00:51:35,164 --> 00:51:37,973
- Today, it was the first day...
- Yes?

1012
00:51:37,974 --> 00:51:39,803
of having you teach us.

1013
00:51:39,804 --> 00:51:42,444
But you taught us really well.

1014
00:51:43,014 --> 00:51:47,184
I felt that you led us well during the acting lesson.

1015
00:51:47,544 --> 00:51:49,753
What a compliment. Thank you.

1016
00:51:49,754 --> 00:51:51,313
Are you sure we're your first students?

1017
00:51:51,314 --> 00:51:53,053
Of course. You're my first students.

1018
00:51:53,054 --> 00:51:54,354
And what does that mean?

1019
00:51:54,454 --> 00:51:56,954
- We'd better do our best.
- You'd better do your best.

1020
00:51:58,224 --> 00:51:59,623
Ha Yun.

1021
00:51:59,624 --> 00:52:01,493
(Next up is Ha Yun.)

1022
00:52:01,494 --> 00:52:02,894
Do you want to pass this time?

1023
00:52:03,364 --> 00:52:05,163
It can be something very simple.

1024
00:52:05,164 --> 00:52:06,603
Don't be pressured.

1025
00:52:06,604 --> 00:52:07,704
- Okay.
- It's...

1026
00:52:08,404 --> 00:52:09,504
Should I shoot you?

1027
00:52:09,604 --> 00:52:11,673
I had fun.

1028
00:52:11,674 --> 00:52:14,044
Did you have fun? That's the best.

1029
00:52:14,244 --> 00:52:15,443
I'm really glad.

1030
00:52:15,444 --> 00:52:17,374
(Shy)

1031
00:52:17,514 --> 00:52:18,674
I'm thankful.

1032
00:52:19,944 --> 00:52:21,844
She was very friendly.

1033
00:52:23,014 --> 00:52:25,184
I like Ms. Kim.

1034
00:52:25,284 --> 00:52:27,524
I'm happy I got to meet a good teacher.

1035
00:52:27,884 --> 00:52:31,624
At first, I thought it was something simple.

1036
00:52:31,954 --> 00:52:35,194
But I was impressed by our teacher's acting.

1037
00:52:35,594 --> 00:52:38,894
I'm happy to be in a play. I think we'll make many memories.

1038
00:52:38,994 --> 00:52:41,034
When it's over,

1039
00:52:41,404 --> 00:52:43,734
I hope to receive huge applause.

1040
00:52:43,834 --> 00:52:45,034
I think it will be electrifying.

1041
00:52:47,504 --> 00:52:48,543
(End of first class)

1042
00:52:48,544 --> 00:52:49,613
Goodbye.

1043
00:52:49,614 --> 00:52:51,243
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

1044
00:52:51,244 --> 00:52:52,244
- See you.
- Bye.

1045
00:52:52,245 --> 00:52:53,584
- Bye.
- Take care.

1046
00:52:53,684 --> 00:52:55,413
- Bye, Eun Soo.
- Bye.

1047
00:52:55,414 --> 00:52:56,713
Bye, Kyung Mo.

1048
00:52:56,714 --> 00:52:57,953
- Bye.
- Bye, Ha Yun.

1049
00:52:57,954 --> 00:53:00,183
Bye, see you tomorrow!

1050
00:53:00,184 --> 00:53:01,924
Bye!

1051
00:53:02,024 --> 00:53:04,654
See you tomorrow, guys!

1052
00:53:27,644 --> 00:53:30,514
(Sighing)

1053
00:53:35,784 --> 00:53:37,624
I'm so tired, and my mouth is dry.

1054
00:53:40,794 --> 00:53:41,794
Seriously.

1055
00:53:41,795 --> 00:53:45,964
(The packed first class is over.)

1056
00:53:50,304 --> 00:53:55,574
(Only silence fills the classroom.)

1057
00:53:58,714 --> 00:54:01,344
I had mixed feelings.

1058
00:54:03,414 --> 00:54:05,813
The class went smoother...

1059
00:54:05,814 --> 00:54:07,584
than what I expected,

1060
00:54:07,684 --> 00:54:09,894
and we were able...

1061
00:54:09,994 --> 00:54:12,594
to go through everything I had planned.

1062
00:54:13,024 --> 00:54:16,694
The children left while cheerfully saying bye.

1063
00:54:17,064 --> 00:54:19,364
But for some reason, I felt empty.

1064
00:54:19,864 --> 00:54:23,634
I was dissatisfied, and something felt unsettling.

1065
00:54:25,104 --> 00:54:27,374
What could this be about?

1066
00:54:27,944 --> 00:54:30,744
I didn't think it would be right to continue this way.

1067
00:54:35,044 --> 00:54:36,783
(Tae Ri's thoughts of determination before beginning the class)

1068
00:54:36,784 --> 00:54:37,884
How should I put it? My thoughts?

1069
00:54:41,784 --> 00:54:43,293
It's not about the kids,

1070
00:54:43,294 --> 00:54:44,894
but about me.

1071
00:54:50,794 --> 00:54:51,994
I want to enjoy it.

1072
00:54:52,534 --> 00:54:54,864
That is the only thing.

1073
00:54:55,364 --> 00:54:58,334
It's the only thing I want to persist.

1074
00:55:00,704 --> 00:55:03,013
I think I have to enjoy it for the kids to enjoy it too.

1075
00:55:03,014 --> 00:55:04,044
- Right.
- Yes.

1076
00:55:07,114 --> 00:55:08,114
But...

1077
00:55:09,754 --> 00:55:11,014
I wasn't enjoying it.

1078
00:55:18,554 --> 00:55:19,724
It feels like a dream.

1079
00:55:30,234 --> 00:55:33,644
(She's suddenly feeling hungry.)

1080
00:55:42,144 --> 00:55:44,984
(There is a car slowly approaching.)

1081
00:55:50,654 --> 00:55:51,654
(Screaming)

1082
00:55:56,664 --> 00:56:00,134
(Who is Tae Ri so happy to welcome?)

1083
00:56:02,534 --> 00:56:05,304
(The guest is...)

1084
00:56:08,504 --> 00:56:09,574
Tae Ri!

1085
00:56:12,867 --> 00:56:15,677
(The guest is...)

1086
00:56:18,747 --> 00:56:19,747
Tae Ri!

1087
00:56:23,187 --> 00:56:24,246
Tae Ri.

1088
00:56:24,247 --> 00:56:26,917
(His words make our hearts flutter.)

1089
00:56:27,387 --> 00:56:29,686
This is crazy. It's so nice!

1090
00:56:29,687 --> 00:56:30,986
(A cheerful younger man has arrived.)

1091
00:56:30,987 --> 00:56:31,987
Hello.

1092
00:56:31,988 --> 00:56:33,197
(Politely greeting)

1093
00:56:33,557 --> 00:56:34,557
Are you well?

1094
00:56:35,597 --> 00:56:36,597
Hello.

1095
00:56:39,597 --> 00:56:43,137
(Someone came to support Tae Ri who was enduring on her own.)

1096
00:56:43,237 --> 00:56:44,737
Yes. Amazing.

1097
00:56:45,267 --> 00:56:46,267
Hello.

1098
00:56:47,037 --> 00:56:49,037
I'm Choi Hyun Wook.

1099
00:56:49,407 --> 00:56:50,947
I'm an actor.

1100
00:56:51,047 --> 00:56:53,106
I was born in 2002. I'm 24.

1101
00:56:53,107 --> 00:56:54,217
(Actor Choi Hyun Wook)

1102
00:56:55,217 --> 00:56:59,717
(The leading man in the music video of "Ditto")

1103
00:57:01,017 --> 00:57:04,687
(He is a key character in "Weak Hero.")

1104
00:57:05,587 --> 00:57:08,797
(He has also starred in "D.P.2" among many others.)

1105
00:57:09,557 --> 00:57:12,097
(An actor who leaves a strong impression)

1106
00:57:12,467 --> 00:57:14,237
Who could you be?

1107
00:57:14,337 --> 00:57:16,437
(So who is Choi Hyun Wook?)

1108
00:57:17,637 --> 00:57:20,507
(He is a scaredy-cat.)

1109
00:57:20,607 --> 00:57:21,637
(Bee!)

1110
00:57:22,707 --> 00:57:23,806
It burst.

1111
00:57:23,807 --> 00:57:26,046
(He makes a lot of mistakes.)

1112
00:57:26,047 --> 00:57:27,047
Hey!

1113
00:57:27,048 --> 00:57:28,677
(Sighing)

1114
00:57:29,447 --> 00:57:32,087
(Twenty-five is a beautiful age.)

1115
00:57:32,747 --> 00:57:34,087
(I can't show this to anyone.)

1116
00:57:34,957 --> 00:57:36,626
(My name is Choi Hyun Wook.)

1117
00:57:36,627 --> 00:57:38,087
(You should shout it out loud too.)

1118
00:57:39,227 --> 00:57:40,497
(Scolding)

1119
00:57:41,857 --> 00:57:43,996
(He even gets scolded by kids.)

1120
00:57:43,997 --> 00:57:47,066
I've never taught anyone before.

1121
00:57:47,067 --> 00:57:49,037
(Rookie teacher Hyun Wook)

1122
00:57:49,867 --> 00:57:51,036
I'm first!

1123
00:57:51,037 --> 00:57:52,606
I hope I'll be approachable to them.

1124
00:57:52,607 --> 00:57:54,276
- Is it fun?
- Yes.

1125
00:57:54,277 --> 00:57:57,777
My wish is to become friends with them.

1126
00:57:58,947 --> 00:58:00,446
(I used to fight a lot and cry a lot too...)

1127
00:58:00,447 --> 00:58:01,447
(during elementary school.)

1128
00:58:01,547 --> 00:58:02,916
(Are you okay?)

1129
00:58:02,917 --> 00:58:03,917
(Do you think you can do it?)

1130
00:58:03,918 --> 00:58:08,487
I'm growing more fond of the kids and I care for them more now.

1131
00:58:08,787 --> 00:58:10,587
I know I came here to teach,

1132
00:58:11,187 --> 00:58:14,357
but I have a feeling I'll learn a lot.

1133
00:58:16,257 --> 00:58:19,027
(A warm-hearted crybaby)

1134
00:58:20,297 --> 00:58:23,506
(Hyun Wook will grow into a sweet teacher.)

1135
00:58:23,507 --> 00:58:26,166
All of you, close your eyes! Turn around!

1136
00:58:26,167 --> 00:58:30,577
I've known Tae Ri for about 3 or 4 years.

1137
00:58:30,777 --> 00:58:32,607
We're good friends.

1138
00:58:33,317 --> 00:58:34,976
(Good friends?)

1139
00:58:34,977 --> 00:58:36,886
I did a drama series with him...

1140
00:58:36,887 --> 00:58:38,746
called "Twenty-Five Twenty-One."

1141
00:58:38,747 --> 00:58:39,947
(They met through "Twenty-Five Twenty-One.")

1142
00:58:40,957 --> 00:58:43,957
(They're 12 years apart in age, but acted as classmates.)

1143
00:58:45,127 --> 00:58:47,697
When I first met Hyun Wook,

1144
00:58:47,997 --> 00:58:50,027
I was extremely nosy.

1145
00:58:51,627 --> 00:58:54,066
I wanted him to do well,

1146
00:58:54,067 --> 00:58:57,667
so I was very nosy in giving him advice.

1147
00:58:57,867 --> 00:59:01,137
Luckily, he was grateful to take my advice.

1148
00:59:01,407 --> 00:59:06,347
They were advices I had never heard before.

1149
00:59:06,777 --> 00:59:09,317
So Tae Ri is the only one...

1150
00:59:09,417 --> 00:59:12,787
I share my worries with.

1151
00:59:13,487 --> 00:59:15,617
Do you always listen to what she says?

1152
00:59:15,717 --> 00:59:17,426
- I don't think so.
- You don't?

1153
00:59:17,427 --> 00:59:19,586
I think I say...

1154
00:59:19,587 --> 00:59:21,427
what's on my mind.

1155
00:59:22,627 --> 00:59:23,666
This is new to me.

1156
00:59:23,667 --> 00:59:24,667
(Meeting before beginning of the acting class)

1157
00:59:24,668 --> 00:59:25,697
Hello.

1158
00:59:26,227 --> 00:59:27,397
Why are you doing this?

1159
00:59:28,597 --> 00:59:29,636
- Hyun Wook.
- Yes?

1160
00:59:29,637 --> 00:59:31,137
How much did they tell you?

1161
00:59:32,007 --> 00:59:36,107
We'll teach, go on outings, and go camping.

1162
00:59:36,437 --> 00:59:38,406
Teach, go on outings, and go camping?

1163
00:59:38,407 --> 00:59:39,506
(Headache)

1164
00:59:39,507 --> 00:59:43,117
And cook too. Something like that.

1165
00:59:44,287 --> 00:59:45,287
That sounds like fun.

1166
00:59:45,288 --> 00:59:47,956
I'd be grateful if you could tell me...

1167
00:59:47,957 --> 00:59:49,857
what I should do during class.

1168
00:59:51,257 --> 00:59:53,626
You're the assistant teacher.

1169
00:59:53,627 --> 00:59:54,627
(Assistant Teacher Hyun Wook)

1170
00:59:54,628 --> 00:59:56,327
I'm the main teacher,

1171
00:59:56,897 --> 00:59:58,766
- so I have work cut out for me.
- Okay.

1172
00:59:58,767 --> 01:00:02,537
So for the very first time, I intend...

1173
01:00:02,897 --> 01:00:04,406
on depending on you a lot.

1174
01:00:04,407 --> 01:00:06,467
- Really?
- You'll have a lot to do.

1175
01:00:06,937 --> 01:00:07,937
I'm okay with it.

1176
01:00:07,938 --> 01:00:11,006
I want us to have a chant.

1177
01:00:11,007 --> 01:00:12,506
Will you prepare the stretches?

1178
01:00:12,507 --> 01:00:16,217
You might have to teach them some dances...

1179
01:00:16,417 --> 01:00:18,846
- because...
- What are you doing, then?

1180
01:00:18,847 --> 01:00:20,456
(What does the main teacher do?)

1181
01:00:20,457 --> 01:00:23,986
I have to have a good understanding of everything from start to finish.

1182
01:00:23,987 --> 01:00:26,586
I need to steer this boat to our destination.

1183
01:00:26,587 --> 01:00:28,896
- So everything aside from that...
- Everything?

1184
01:00:28,897 --> 01:00:30,596
Everything aside from that...

1185
01:00:30,597 --> 01:00:32,196
are just as important.

1186
01:00:32,197 --> 01:00:33,936
- They're important.
- Very important.

1187
01:00:33,937 --> 01:00:36,567
I need you to cover them...

1188
01:00:36,937 --> 01:00:39,066
really quickly.

1189
01:00:39,067 --> 01:00:40,306
So what are you going to be doing?

1190
01:00:40,307 --> 01:00:41,537
(So what are you going to be doing?)

1191
01:00:41,607 --> 01:00:43,137
Command? Direct?

1192
01:00:43,647 --> 01:00:44,947
Yes!

1193
01:00:45,207 --> 01:00:47,016
I'm the captain.

1194
01:00:47,017 --> 01:00:50,016
You have to take care of the kids.

1195
01:00:50,017 --> 01:00:53,016
Send them to the bathroom, and remind them of the supplies.

1196
01:00:53,017 --> 01:00:54,756
There is more work than I thought.

1197
01:00:54,757 --> 01:00:56,686
You have to attend to them...

1198
01:00:56,687 --> 01:00:58,087
as well as attend to me.

1199
01:00:59,027 --> 01:01:01,696
- I just want to know...
- You thought it was simple.

1200
01:01:01,697 --> 01:01:03,397
what you're doing.

1201
01:01:03,997 --> 01:01:05,826
I have to steer.

1202
01:01:05,827 --> 01:01:08,537
(I have to steer.)

1203
01:01:10,707 --> 01:01:11,907
Is that all?

1204
01:01:12,867 --> 01:01:16,276
On about day 5 or 6, I want you...

1205
01:01:16,277 --> 01:01:17,806
to take over everything...

1206
01:01:17,807 --> 01:01:19,946
for one day.

1207
01:01:19,947 --> 01:01:22,016
I want you to have a difficult day.

1208
01:01:22,017 --> 01:01:23,817
I want you to cry from all the hardships.

1209
01:01:23,917 --> 01:01:24,947
I mean it.

1210
01:01:25,187 --> 01:01:28,057
I want her to cry from being exhausted.

1211
01:01:28,587 --> 01:01:29,887
I really want that.

1212
01:01:30,457 --> 01:01:31,587
But why?

1213
01:01:31,957 --> 01:01:32,987
It's fun.

1214
01:01:33,597 --> 01:01:34,597
Something like that.

1215
01:01:34,598 --> 01:01:37,467
(They're like real siblings.)

1216
01:01:38,527 --> 01:01:40,167
I hope we don't fall apart.

1217
01:01:42,867 --> 01:01:43,937
I hope not.

1218
01:01:46,167 --> 01:01:47,436
This is amazing.

1219
01:01:47,437 --> 01:01:49,506
(Anyway, their roommate life starts now.)

1220
01:01:49,507 --> 01:01:50,507
Here.

1221
01:01:50,508 --> 01:01:52,276
- It's really starting.
- I'll put it here for now.

1222
01:01:52,277 --> 01:01:53,306
Okay.

1223
01:01:53,307 --> 01:01:54,317
(Moving in with excitement)

1224
01:01:54,647 --> 01:01:56,987
Ta-da!

1225
01:01:57,087 --> 01:01:58,487
This is the livingroom.

1226
01:01:58,917 --> 01:02:00,556
I see.

1227
01:02:00,557 --> 01:02:03,286
- This is my room.
- Okay.

1228
01:02:03,287 --> 01:02:04,627
And what does that mean?

1229
01:02:04,927 --> 01:02:05,987
Where do I sleep?

1230
01:02:08,457 --> 01:02:09,526
Here, where else?

1231
01:02:09,527 --> 01:02:12,166
(Your room must be here.)

1232
01:02:12,167 --> 01:02:13,667
- I see.
- Where else?

1233
01:02:13,737 --> 01:02:15,836
- Is this it?
- Don't you agree?

1234
01:02:15,837 --> 01:02:17,106
Or this.

1235
01:02:17,107 --> 01:02:18,937
- Great.
- Is it great?

1236
01:02:19,637 --> 01:02:21,707
This is how it works.

1237
01:02:23,577 --> 01:02:24,646
(Their spaces are separated.)

1238
01:02:24,647 --> 01:02:25,876
- Like that?
- Yes.

1239
01:02:25,877 --> 01:02:27,447
Hyun Wook.

1240
01:02:27,517 --> 01:02:28,576
(Relieved)

1241
01:02:28,577 --> 01:02:29,617
Yes, Tae Ri?

1242
01:02:30,487 --> 01:02:33,117
(Their privacy is perfectly protected.)

1243
01:02:33,247 --> 01:02:36,417
All right. Tell me what you think is strange about this space.

1244
01:02:36,517 --> 01:02:37,586
What is it?

1245
01:02:37,587 --> 01:02:38,756
Don't you find something strange?

1246
01:02:38,757 --> 01:02:40,056
(There's more?)

1247
01:02:40,057 --> 01:02:42,427
- I don't know.
- Aren't we missing something?

1248
01:02:42,997 --> 01:02:44,096
What is it?

1249
01:02:44,097 --> 01:02:45,126
(Something is missing in this house.)

1250
01:02:45,127 --> 01:02:46,127
I don't know.

1251
01:02:46,527 --> 01:02:48,536
- The bathroom.
- Where is the bathroom?

1252
01:02:48,537 --> 01:02:49,797
Where is the bathroom?

1253
01:02:51,467 --> 01:02:52,507
Where is the bathroom?

1254
01:02:53,037 --> 01:02:54,807
- Do you see that over there?
- Is that it?

1255
01:02:54,937 --> 01:02:55,937
Yes.

1256
01:02:57,177 --> 01:02:59,046
(His love for the house is peaking.)

1257
01:02:59,047 --> 01:03:00,147
You can go there.

1258
01:03:00,847 --> 01:03:02,617
What a dynamic space.

1259
01:03:02,847 --> 01:03:03,847
Yes.

1260
01:03:03,887 --> 01:03:06,817
Also, the ricemaker is over there.

1261
01:03:07,057 --> 01:03:09,586
Do you mean the fire pit? There's firewood too.

1262
01:03:09,587 --> 01:03:12,027
Yes. That must be for barbecues. Right?

1263
01:03:13,827 --> 01:03:15,956
(Moved)

1264
01:03:15,957 --> 01:03:18,767
I have nothing to do with this. I have no interest in this.

1265
01:03:18,897 --> 01:03:20,097
This is wonderful.

1266
01:03:20,267 --> 01:03:21,767
Is it? Do you like it?

1267
01:03:22,267 --> 01:03:24,867
I haven't done any fire-making...

1268
01:03:25,307 --> 01:03:26,537
since childhood.

1269
01:03:26,707 --> 01:03:28,276
My goodness.

1270
01:03:28,277 --> 01:03:30,037
(Even the firewood moves him.)

1271
01:03:34,347 --> 01:03:36,017
(He's getting the hang of it.)

1272
01:03:39,117 --> 01:03:41,417
(He is unexpectedly rugged.)

1273
01:03:41,557 --> 01:03:42,717
I'm quite excited.

1274
01:03:43,317 --> 01:03:44,727
- What?
- I'm excited.

1275
01:03:44,957 --> 01:03:46,087
- You?
- Yes.

1276
01:03:46,457 --> 01:03:47,457
I'm so glad.

1277
01:03:48,597 --> 01:03:50,897
It's so amusing and exciting.

1278
01:03:51,127 --> 01:03:52,567
It feels like I'm on vacation.

1279
01:03:53,597 --> 01:03:55,297
I really like this place.

1280
01:03:56,897 --> 01:03:58,807
(From the moment they wake up...)

1281
01:03:59,207 --> 01:04:00,636
(Good work today, Hyun Wook.)

1282
01:04:00,637 --> 01:04:02,577
(to the moment they sleep)

1283
01:04:03,177 --> 01:04:05,047
(They will shop together,)

1284
01:04:05,807 --> 01:04:07,547
(cook together,)

1285
01:04:08,577 --> 01:04:11,287
(dance together,)

1286
01:04:11,817 --> 01:04:13,657
(and be stubborn together.)

1287
01:04:14,317 --> 01:04:16,517
(Happy roommate life)

1288
01:04:16,957 --> 01:04:19,257
Have you been faking it in front of me?

1289
01:04:20,287 --> 01:04:21,357
I'm sorry.

1290
01:04:22,427 --> 01:04:23,427
(Happy roommate life)

1291
01:04:23,428 --> 01:04:24,927
(The collapse of the roommate life)

1292
01:04:25,027 --> 01:04:26,997
- Hyun Wook.
- Are you scolding me?

1293
01:04:27,197 --> 01:04:28,996
I'm not blaming you.

1294
01:04:28,997 --> 01:04:30,197
I'm not either.

1295
01:04:31,707 --> 01:04:35,337
(They'll become someone each other can depend on.)

1296
01:04:36,507 --> 01:04:38,446
How can the kids do it when you can't do it?

1297
01:04:38,447 --> 01:04:39,946
Explain it to me so I can understand.

1298
01:04:39,947 --> 01:04:43,416
(They'll share sincere feelings.)

1299
01:04:43,417 --> 01:04:45,786
You had it easy until now!

1300
01:04:45,787 --> 01:04:48,817
Do you know how much I...

1301
01:04:51,487 --> 01:04:54,196
(The siblings will strengthen their relationship.)

1302
01:04:54,197 --> 01:04:57,727
- I want to go home.
- Are you serious?

1303
01:04:59,297 --> 01:05:01,267
- I'm so excited.
- I'm happy.

1304
01:05:01,397 --> 01:05:03,707
I'm honestly happy.

1305
01:05:04,167 --> 01:05:05,366
That's all that matters.

1306
01:05:05,367 --> 01:05:06,937
(We look forward to these teachers' 16 days.)

1307
01:05:09,977 --> 01:05:13,507
(Preparing for class)

1308
01:05:16,147 --> 01:05:18,186
(Eye contact)

1309
01:05:18,187 --> 01:05:19,217
Gosh.

1310
01:05:21,057 --> 01:05:24,927
(They're not used to the roommate life.)

1311
01:05:26,087 --> 01:05:27,656
Are you going to work some more?

1312
01:05:27,657 --> 01:05:28,697
Yes.

1313
01:05:28,857 --> 01:05:30,226
I'll go wash up.

1314
01:05:30,227 --> 01:05:31,227
Okay.

1315
01:05:41,507 --> 01:05:45,847
I was really dissatisfied with my first class.

1316
01:05:46,047 --> 01:05:48,616
All I had on my mind...

1317
01:05:48,617 --> 01:05:51,447
was that I had to make it happen.

1318
01:05:52,647 --> 01:05:54,286
This is what makes me anxious.

1319
01:05:54,287 --> 01:05:57,756
We don't have enough time.

1320
01:05:57,757 --> 01:06:00,526
The classes need to be effective.

1321
01:06:00,527 --> 01:06:04,026
That's what makes me anxious.

1322
01:06:04,027 --> 01:06:05,797
(Her dissatisfaction with the class led to her anxiousness.)

1323
01:06:08,497 --> 01:06:12,137
(It's finally time for bed.)

1324
01:06:15,637 --> 01:06:16,707
Okay.

1325
01:06:19,607 --> 01:06:23,247
(Or a bedtime story...)

1326
01:06:29,357 --> 01:06:34,827
("The World Called Children" by Kim So Young)

1327
01:06:36,927 --> 01:06:39,066
(Childhood is a time when many things are sculpted...)

1328
01:06:39,067 --> 01:06:41,366
(by adults more than the children themselves.)

1329
01:06:41,367 --> 01:06:43,366
(This period has a huge impact on their lives,)

1330
01:06:43,367 --> 01:06:45,436
(but it cannot be changed, made up, or forgotten.)

1331
01:06:45,437 --> 01:06:48,337
(From "The World Called Children")

1332
01:07:19,707 --> 01:07:25,277
(The excerpt gives her a lot to chew on.)

1333
01:07:48,697 --> 01:07:52,607
(Hyun Wook finished washing up.)

1334
01:07:55,877 --> 01:07:57,006
(What?)

1335
01:07:57,007 --> 01:07:58,046
(What?)

1336
01:07:58,047 --> 01:07:59,507
(What?)

1337
01:08:00,007 --> 01:08:01,377
Come on!

1338
01:08:02,417 --> 01:08:05,617
(He almost ran back home on the first day.)

1339
01:08:06,687 --> 01:08:08,217
You startled me.

1340
01:08:12,257 --> 01:08:13,626
- Aren't you sleepy?
- What?

1341
01:08:13,627 --> 01:08:14,627
Aren't you sleepy?

1342
01:08:14,797 --> 01:08:15,856
Right now?

1343
01:08:15,857 --> 01:08:17,927
Yes and no.

1344
01:08:24,807 --> 01:08:26,937
The school is really beautiful, isn't it?

1345
01:08:27,407 --> 01:08:28,537
It's so pretty.

1346
01:08:30,607 --> 01:08:31,877
Have you been to the classroom?

1347
01:08:32,047 --> 01:08:33,747
Yes, I have.

1348
01:08:33,977 --> 01:08:37,487
But there are no kids in grade one this year.

1349
01:08:37,587 --> 01:08:39,617
- Have you heard?
- No.

1350
01:08:40,657 --> 01:08:42,317
There is no one in the first grade.

1351
01:08:43,717 --> 01:08:47,026
If they can't get any new kids to come to this school...

1352
01:08:47,027 --> 01:08:48,657
within the next two years,

1353
01:08:49,597 --> 01:08:52,626
they'll be at risk of closing down.

1354
01:08:52,627 --> 01:08:55,037
- What can we do?
- That's the situation.

1355
01:08:57,337 --> 01:08:58,636
- Is there...
- Actually...

1356
01:08:58,637 --> 01:09:00,336
But is there something we can do?

1357
01:09:00,337 --> 01:09:03,077
No. There isn't.

1358
01:09:03,507 --> 01:09:04,907
Just...

1359
01:09:07,647 --> 01:09:10,416
It was a coincidence, but now I have met them.

1360
01:09:10,417 --> 01:09:13,986
Should I just take this...

1361
01:09:13,987 --> 01:09:17,657
as a way to help these children...

1362
01:09:17,757 --> 01:09:20,187
make good memories of this school?

1363
01:09:21,127 --> 01:09:23,427
- Yes.
- That's all I can do.

1364
01:09:26,927 --> 01:09:29,237
It hurts me when I see something like this.

1365
01:09:31,767 --> 01:09:32,767
Really.

1366
01:09:39,477 --> 01:09:41,247
But that's the reality in Korea.

1367
01:09:45,417 --> 01:09:46,687
- I was...
- Yes.

1368
01:09:47,087 --> 01:09:48,687
- lying down.
- Okay.

1369
01:09:49,587 --> 01:09:51,927
And I suddenly had this thought.

1370
01:09:52,757 --> 01:09:55,257
I've prepared so much for this.

1371
01:09:56,557 --> 01:10:00,027
Because I didn't think I knew a lot about this area,

1372
01:10:01,597 --> 01:10:03,397
I felt anxious.

1373
01:10:04,937 --> 01:10:07,737
That's why I studied what others do.

1374
01:10:07,837 --> 01:10:11,577
What the people and pros in this field do.

1375
01:10:11,747 --> 01:10:14,117
Those are the things I've studied.

1376
01:10:16,817 --> 01:10:19,087
- So, to do the things...
- To be good at it.

1377
01:10:19,587 --> 01:10:22,487
that others said that were working,

1378
01:10:24,127 --> 01:10:25,727
I couldn't focus on the kids.

1379
01:10:26,187 --> 01:10:27,187
I see.

1380
01:10:28,327 --> 01:10:32,327
I was all by myself during the break.

1381
01:10:32,897 --> 01:10:34,636
Even when they called me,

1382
01:10:34,637 --> 01:10:37,566
I joined them briefly, then I came back and stayed alone.

1383
01:10:37,567 --> 01:10:39,167
- What did you do?
- That happened.

1384
01:10:39,807 --> 01:10:42,177
I didn't do anything. I just zoned out.

1385
01:10:43,207 --> 01:10:46,106
It doesn't make sense.

1386
01:10:46,107 --> 01:10:48,016
To know them...

1387
01:10:48,017 --> 01:10:51,646
and explore them in such a short time,

1388
01:10:51,647 --> 01:10:55,187
that ten-minute break is such a precious time.

1389
01:10:55,457 --> 01:10:56,517
But I...

1390
01:10:57,457 --> 01:10:59,086
I stayed by myself.

1391
01:10:59,087 --> 01:11:01,456
- I don't even know...
- But today...

1392
01:11:01,457 --> 01:11:02,697
where things went wrong.

1393
01:11:03,057 --> 01:11:05,996
That's how wrong this is.

1394
01:11:05,997 --> 01:11:08,637
It was your first day, and this is your first time.

1395
01:11:08,967 --> 01:11:11,137
You must have been nervous.

1396
01:11:11,207 --> 01:11:12,807
I was really worried about you.

1397
01:11:13,937 --> 01:11:15,907
The play is the issue.

1398
01:11:16,807 --> 01:11:19,847
I do want to put on a play that has a good quality.

1399
01:11:20,047 --> 01:11:21,546
- It's because...
- I totally understand.

1400
01:11:21,547 --> 01:11:25,517
Because I've always wanted to do something good.

1401
01:11:25,747 --> 01:11:26,787
Something good.

1402
01:11:28,457 --> 01:11:29,457
Honestly,

1403
01:11:30,417 --> 01:11:31,727
I don't want to look lame.

1404
01:11:33,387 --> 01:11:34,827
That's how I feel.

1405
01:11:34,997 --> 01:11:36,297
But that's...

1406
01:11:37,157 --> 01:11:38,397
contradicting.

1407
01:11:39,397 --> 01:11:42,867
The curriculum I've prepared and the things that need to be done.

1408
01:11:43,497 --> 01:11:45,707
Because I was doing what others did,

1409
01:11:46,007 --> 01:11:49,637
I think it was hard for me...

1410
01:11:50,107 --> 01:11:53,776
to look at the students with sincerity.

1411
01:11:53,777 --> 01:11:55,047
(It was hard to be sincere.)

1412
01:11:55,347 --> 01:11:58,717
I think the time we have will be precious...

1413
01:11:59,217 --> 01:12:00,587
because it'll pass.

1414
01:12:02,457 --> 01:12:04,357
What are the things...

1415
01:12:05,327 --> 01:12:07,157
I can tell these students now?

1416
01:12:08,127 --> 01:12:09,327
"I want to provide..."

1417
01:12:09,627 --> 01:12:12,867
"great experiences and memories that will help them..."

1418
01:12:13,097 --> 01:12:16,937
"when they go about their lives in the future."

1419
01:12:17,907 --> 01:12:20,407
That's how I should feel when I look at them.

1420
01:12:21,237 --> 01:12:24,406
That's why after thinking about...

1421
01:12:24,407 --> 01:12:26,107
- what I can do here, - Yes.

1422
01:12:26,447 --> 01:12:30,546
I thought I should do it in a way that is different from yours.

1423
01:12:30,547 --> 01:12:31,547
Yes.

1424
01:12:31,647 --> 01:12:36,357
I'll try to do it in the ways I can.

1425
01:12:37,827 --> 01:12:41,356
I think I should relax a bit.

1426
01:12:41,357 --> 01:12:44,897
I like how you are right now because I can make fun of it.

1427
01:12:45,027 --> 01:12:46,627
How I'm trying my best?

1428
01:12:46,867 --> 01:12:47,937
Darn it.

1429
01:12:49,997 --> 01:12:51,867
(Yawning)

1430
01:12:52,637 --> 01:12:53,807
What was that?

1431
01:12:57,277 --> 01:12:58,946
Should we go back? It's getting cold.

1432
01:12:58,947 --> 01:13:00,376
Yes. Let's go.

1433
01:13:00,377 --> 01:13:01,517
(Now, it's really time to sleep.)

1434
01:13:04,077 --> 01:13:05,247
Good night, Tae Ri.

1435
01:13:05,647 --> 01:13:06,687
All right.

1436
01:13:10,557 --> 01:13:12,257
This feels like a dream. Seriously.

1437
01:13:13,557 --> 01:13:14,627
I think it's fun.

1438
01:13:15,427 --> 01:13:16,796
- Good night.
- Good night.

1439
01:13:16,797 --> 01:13:20,666
(The night of sharing thoughts and concerns has passed.)

1440
01:13:20,667 --> 01:13:22,696
(Sesol Hall)

1441
01:13:22,697 --> 01:13:25,967
The second day has come. A train wreck is expected...

1442
01:13:26,337 --> 01:13:27,736
to happen in the second class.

1443
01:13:27,737 --> 01:13:28,737
(The second day of class)

1444
01:13:29,437 --> 01:13:30,907
Hyo Min, Ha Yun.

1445
01:13:31,207 --> 01:13:33,246
- Kyung Mo, Eun Su.
- Hyo Min, Ha Yun.

1446
01:13:33,247 --> 01:13:35,047
- Won Jin.
- Hyo Min, Ha Yun.

1447
01:13:35,517 --> 01:13:36,916
Ju Eun, Hyo Min.

1448
01:13:36,917 --> 01:13:37,987
(Nervous)

1449
01:13:38,287 --> 01:13:40,517
- Ha Yun.
- Okay. One more time.

1450
01:13:44,787 --> 01:13:45,787
(2nd class!)

1451
01:13:45,788 --> 01:13:48,226
(Today's keywords: Wind and journey)

1452
01:13:48,227 --> 01:13:49,357
What should I do now?

1453
01:13:50,657 --> 01:13:54,667
I think it'll be good to make the path for the journey.

1454
01:13:54,897 --> 01:13:56,836
Let's make a path...

1455
01:13:56,837 --> 01:13:58,836
- with those in the break.
- Sounds good.

1456
01:13:58,837 --> 01:14:01,537
The path can go like this.

1457
01:14:02,107 --> 01:14:03,976
- Something like this.
- Yes.

1458
01:14:03,977 --> 01:14:05,207
(Mr. Choi's task 1: Setting up the path during the break)

1459
01:14:05,877 --> 01:14:07,947
- Do we warm up here?
- What?

1460
01:14:08,277 --> 01:14:09,617
Do we do the warm-up here?

1461
01:14:10,017 --> 01:14:11,047
Yes.

1462
01:14:12,687 --> 01:14:16,117
(He got the video from Tae Ri.)

1463
01:14:18,027 --> 01:14:20,127
(Bouncing)

1464
01:14:27,267 --> 01:14:28,437
What's after this?

1465
01:14:30,937 --> 01:14:32,007
I don't know, dude.

1466
01:14:32,567 --> 01:14:33,737
Do I really do this?

1467
01:14:35,007 --> 01:14:36,207
Do I really do this?

1468
01:14:37,377 --> 01:14:39,606
- I told you to be prepared for it.
- Okay. I'll do it.

1469
01:14:39,607 --> 01:14:41,117
Are you going to make my heart jump?

1470
01:14:41,477 --> 01:14:43,247
My heart is racing.

1471
01:14:43,547 --> 01:14:44,647
I can do it.

1472
01:14:44,987 --> 01:14:47,857
Seriously. My heart is beating fast.

1473
01:14:48,487 --> 01:14:50,117
Don't make me panic.

1474
01:14:50,757 --> 01:14:51,956
I'm curious about the kids.

1475
01:14:51,957 --> 01:14:53,226
(Will Mr. Choi's first class go smoothly?)

1476
01:14:53,227 --> 01:14:54,397
How will they react?

1477
01:14:56,497 --> 01:14:58,696
It's the day of the second class today.

1478
01:14:58,697 --> 01:15:00,897
(It's the day of the second class today.)

1479
01:15:02,067 --> 01:15:04,937
(They're getting along well today too.)

1480
01:15:05,567 --> 01:15:07,876
I took a dictation test today.

1481
01:15:07,877 --> 01:15:09,877
- And I got 90 points.
- Okay.

1482
01:15:11,647 --> 01:15:12,776
Hey, hurry.

1483
01:15:12,777 --> 01:15:14,746
- Does anyone have it?
- Let's hurry.

1484
01:15:14,747 --> 01:15:16,277
Ms. Kim!

1485
01:15:16,417 --> 01:15:17,887
Hello!

1486
01:15:18,547 --> 01:15:19,816
- Gosh.
- I like it too.

1487
01:15:19,817 --> 01:15:21,487
Everyone!

1488
01:15:21,817 --> 01:15:23,186
Actually, today,

1489
01:15:23,187 --> 01:15:26,957
there is something you will love about.

1490
01:15:27,627 --> 01:15:29,896
We're working together...

1491
01:15:29,897 --> 01:15:32,597
only for a short time to create a play.

1492
01:15:32,697 --> 01:15:37,067
So, I might not be able to handle it alone.

1493
01:15:37,167 --> 01:15:39,867
Therefore, I invited my colleague.

1494
01:15:40,107 --> 01:15:43,137
An assistant teacher will come.

1495
01:15:43,337 --> 01:15:44,547
- But...
- Who would it be?

1496
01:15:44,677 --> 01:15:47,347
- Who?
- where will he make an entrance?

1497
01:15:47,607 --> 01:15:48,846
- Backstage.
- From the back of the stage.

1498
01:15:48,847 --> 01:15:50,616
- From the stage?
- Over there.

1499
01:15:50,617 --> 01:15:52,047
- There!
- Are you guessing an empty space?

1500
01:15:52,317 --> 01:15:54,387
- You're wrong.
- From a restroom.

1501
01:15:54,417 --> 01:15:56,217
Did you hear the knock?

1502
01:15:57,257 --> 01:15:57,944
Over there!

1503
01:15:58,003 --> 01:15:59,962
- You're wrong.
- From a restroom.

1504
01:15:59,963 --> 01:16:01,933
Did you hear the knock?

1505
01:16:03,003 --> 01:16:04,032
- Over there!
- There!

1506
01:16:04,033 --> 01:16:05,103
- I found it!
- There!

1507
01:16:05,543 --> 01:16:07,072
Everyone, let's welcome him.

1508
01:16:07,073 --> 01:16:08,842
- Let's go!
- Go!

1509
01:16:08,843 --> 01:16:10,313
- Go!
- Who is it?

1510
01:16:10,443 --> 01:16:12,243
- Hello.
- Hello!

1511
01:16:12,613 --> 01:16:14,112
(Hello.)

1512
01:16:14,113 --> 01:16:17,822
- Hello.
- Hello.

1513
01:16:17,823 --> 01:16:20,022
- Hello.
- Should we guide him here?

1514
01:16:20,023 --> 01:16:21,923
- I think I've seen him somewhere.
- Hello.

1515
01:16:22,653 --> 01:16:24,862
- Take him here quickly.
- He's taller than I thought.

1516
01:16:24,863 --> 01:16:26,892
- Hurry.
- He's really tall.

1517
01:16:26,893 --> 01:16:28,893
- Hello.
- I hope my teacher looks like that.

1518
01:16:29,663 --> 01:16:31,333
He hopes his teacher looks like him.

1519
01:16:32,263 --> 01:16:34,202
This teacher's name...

1520
01:16:34,203 --> 01:16:37,002
is Choi Hyun Wook.

1521
01:16:37,003 --> 01:16:39,102
His nickname is a potato.

1522
01:16:39,103 --> 01:16:40,643
You all have nicknames too, right?

1523
01:16:41,243 --> 01:16:42,342
Mine is a sparrow.

1524
01:16:42,343 --> 01:16:44,312
- Sparrow? That's cute.
- Because I scream a lot.

1525
01:16:44,313 --> 01:16:46,212
- My name is...
- Call him Potato Teacher.

1526
01:16:46,213 --> 01:16:47,683
Potato Teacher.

1527
01:16:47,953 --> 01:16:49,182
Why is it Potato Teacher?

1528
01:16:49,183 --> 01:16:51,622
My nickname was a potato when I was young...

1529
01:16:51,623 --> 01:16:53,223
because I had a round face.

1530
01:16:53,623 --> 01:16:55,793
That's why people called me a potato.

1531
01:16:56,423 --> 01:16:57,993
You can call me Potato Teacher.

1532
01:16:58,293 --> 01:17:01,992
Potato Teacher has brought a gift for you.

1533
01:17:01,993 --> 01:17:03,233
What would it be?

1534
01:17:03,433 --> 01:17:05,833
- What is it? A ticket for a play?
- A ticket for a play?

1535
01:17:06,263 --> 01:17:07,433
A play script!

1536
01:17:08,803 --> 01:17:09,903
- Koo Ja Wook? No.
- Cha...

1537
01:17:10,533 --> 01:17:11,772
Chant!

1538
01:17:11,773 --> 01:17:15,442
He has made an awesome chant for us!

1539
01:17:15,443 --> 01:17:17,513
You should look forward to it!

1540
01:17:17,713 --> 01:17:20,013
When I say, "From today,"

1541
01:17:20,413 --> 01:17:22,382
you say, "we are..."

1542
01:17:22,383 --> 01:17:24,053
and together we say, "one!"

1543
01:17:24,383 --> 01:17:25,423
And...

1544
01:17:25,753 --> 01:17:26,923
(Laughing)

1545
01:17:27,283 --> 01:17:29,393
"We can do it. Let's go! Hooray!"

1546
01:17:29,993 --> 01:17:31,593
- That's all.
- It's longer than I thought.

1547
01:17:31,963 --> 01:17:33,122
Let's try it. Okay?

1548
01:17:33,123 --> 01:17:34,533
Please shout it out loud.

1549
01:17:34,793 --> 01:17:36,892
- Let's imagine this is a field day.
- A field day.

1550
01:17:36,893 --> 01:17:37,962
- Okay?
- Yes.

1551
01:17:37,963 --> 01:17:39,802
You should shout it out loud too.

1552
01:17:39,803 --> 01:17:41,272
- You should say it louder too.
- Yes.

1553
01:17:41,273 --> 01:17:43,202
You should shout it out loud too.

1554
01:17:43,203 --> 01:17:44,743
You should say it louder too.

1555
01:17:45,403 --> 01:17:47,602
Speak it out loud even if the mic doesn't work.

1556
01:17:47,603 --> 01:17:49,673
It'll be all shot for the show.

1557
01:17:49,873 --> 01:17:50,873
You'll be on the show,

1558
01:17:50,874 --> 01:17:53,013
so please do it right, Potato Teacher.

1559
01:17:53,313 --> 01:17:56,053
- They know it will be aired.
- Okay.

1560
01:17:56,253 --> 01:17:57,782
I'll say it louder too.

1561
01:17:57,783 --> 01:17:59,023
- Good job.
- Yes.

1562
01:18:00,683 --> 01:18:01,992
Volume up!

1563
01:18:01,993 --> 01:18:03,392
(Go, Potato Teacher!)

1564
01:18:03,393 --> 01:18:04,492
Louder.

1565
01:18:04,493 --> 01:18:06,563
From today, we are...

1566
01:18:06,723 --> 01:18:08,092
- One!
- One!

1567
01:18:08,093 --> 01:18:10,432
- We can do it!
- We can do it!

1568
01:18:10,433 --> 01:18:12,633
- Let's go! Hooray!
- Let's go! Hooray!

1569
01:18:13,503 --> 01:18:16,002
- I think we'll scream a lot.
- Isn't this so much fun?

1570
01:18:16,003 --> 01:18:17,372
(A shocking introduction of the Potato)

1571
01:18:17,373 --> 01:18:19,402
Now, before we perform a play,

1572
01:18:19,403 --> 01:18:21,612
we always have to warm up.

1573
01:18:21,613 --> 01:18:25,212
Starting today, he'll help us warm up. Who is he?

1574
01:18:25,213 --> 01:18:26,582
- Mr. Choi!
- Potato Teacher!

1575
01:18:26,583 --> 01:18:29,013
- Potato Teacher.
- I'm Potato Teacher.

1576
01:18:29,813 --> 01:18:31,883
Kids, we'll do the warm-up.

1577
01:18:32,123 --> 01:18:33,552
You can spread out.

1578
01:18:33,553 --> 01:18:35,352
- Spread out.
- Let's spread out.

1579
01:18:35,353 --> 01:18:37,552
- Yes!
- How do we warm up?

1580
01:18:37,553 --> 01:18:41,532
Okay. I'll play the music. And I'll teach you the dance moves.

1581
01:18:41,533 --> 01:18:43,533
And we'll do it together.

1582
01:18:43,733 --> 01:18:45,733
I'll play the music.

1583
01:18:47,163 --> 01:18:48,173
Okay.

1584
01:18:49,733 --> 01:18:51,173
You can do it like this.

1585
01:18:51,273 --> 01:18:53,003
(Shy)

1586
01:18:57,573 --> 01:18:58,582
What?

1587
01:18:58,583 --> 01:18:59,613
Hold on.

1588
01:18:59,743 --> 01:19:00,843
Next... Hey.

1589
01:19:03,083 --> 01:19:04,623
What is this?

1590
01:19:04,783 --> 01:19:06,453
- It's weird.
- What is this?

1591
01:19:07,283 --> 01:19:08,393
To the side!

1592
01:19:11,223 --> 01:19:13,223
- Go back!
- What is this?

1593
01:19:14,763 --> 01:19:15,792
Hey!

1594
01:19:15,793 --> 01:19:16,932
(The most excited one)

1595
01:19:16,933 --> 01:19:19,532
Let's go back to our spot. Go back.

1596
01:19:19,533 --> 01:19:20,633
Return to your spot.

1597
01:19:21,433 --> 01:19:22,573
One more time. Hey!

1598
01:19:24,433 --> 01:19:26,202
(Whatever.)

1599
01:19:26,203 --> 01:19:27,403
Gosh.

1600
01:19:28,143 --> 01:19:29,813
You can stand still at the end.

1601
01:19:30,943 --> 01:19:32,313
That's all. How was it?

1602
01:19:33,113 --> 01:19:34,212
- Isn't it fun?
- It's hard.

1603
01:19:34,213 --> 01:19:36,182
Please choose a different song.

1604
01:19:36,183 --> 01:19:37,853
- A different song?
- Please.

1605
01:19:41,823 --> 01:19:42,823
I don't know.

1606
01:19:43,693 --> 01:19:45,622
I thought I wouldn't be nervous.

1607
01:19:45,623 --> 01:19:48,793
I was just excited.

1608
01:19:49,133 --> 01:19:52,263
I was excited to meet the elementary school students.

1609
01:19:52,663 --> 01:19:54,533
But now that I'm here, I'm so nervous.

1610
01:19:56,173 --> 01:19:58,573
I think I should try harder. Yes.

1611
01:19:59,743 --> 01:20:01,242
From now on,

1612
01:20:01,243 --> 01:20:04,142
we'll become wind.

1613
01:20:04,143 --> 01:20:05,182
(WIND)

1614
01:20:05,183 --> 01:20:06,183
Wind? Or...

1615
01:20:06,183 --> 01:20:07,183
Mr. Choi, give one...

1616
01:20:07,184 --> 01:20:09,382
- to each student.
- What?

1617
01:20:09,383 --> 01:20:12,583
Okay. Imagine that this is the wind.

1618
01:20:12,683 --> 01:20:14,792
- Okay.
- Look at how the clothes look.

1619
01:20:14,793 --> 01:20:16,052
How does it feel?

1620
01:20:16,053 --> 01:20:17,492
- Keep that in mind. Okay?
- Ms. Kim,

1621
01:20:17,493 --> 01:20:18,762
isn't this a sponge?

1622
01:20:18,763 --> 01:20:20,722
You're right. It does look like a sponge.

1623
01:20:20,723 --> 01:20:22,493
- Isn't it a steel scouring pad?
- Right?

1624
01:20:22,663 --> 01:20:24,293
It will foam well, won't it?

1625
01:20:25,363 --> 01:20:27,362
Move freely...

1626
01:20:27,363 --> 01:20:30,173
and feel the cloth.

1627
01:20:30,603 --> 01:20:32,042
- That's it.
- It's wind.

1628
01:20:32,043 --> 01:20:33,173
Move freely.

1629
01:20:33,473 --> 01:20:34,542
You can walk.

1630
01:20:34,543 --> 01:20:35,842
- You can twirl it too.
- Ms. Kim!

1631
01:20:35,843 --> 01:20:37,342
- Feel it.
- Look!

1632
01:20:37,343 --> 01:20:38,343
- Look at this.
- I want to do this.

1633
01:20:38,943 --> 01:20:40,682
Everyone, stop!

1634
01:20:40,683 --> 01:20:42,453
(Stop!)

1635
01:20:43,213 --> 01:20:46,682
Now, the wind will blow calmly.

1636
01:20:46,683 --> 01:20:48,893
And you'll sit on the wind.

1637
01:20:49,423 --> 01:20:53,323
I talked about the wind today...

1638
01:20:53,893 --> 01:20:56,863
because I'm finally going to tell you...

1639
01:20:57,133 --> 01:21:00,503
what play we'll perform on stage.

1640
01:21:01,163 --> 01:21:03,973
This story is called "The Wizard of Oz."

1641
01:21:04,773 --> 01:21:06,942
"The Wizard of Oz." Does anyone know about it?

1642
01:21:06,943 --> 01:21:08,142
- What is it?
- Yes.

1643
01:21:08,143 --> 01:21:09,543
Raise your hand if you know it.

1644
01:21:09,743 --> 01:21:11,272
Some might know about it.

1645
01:21:11,273 --> 01:21:13,282
- I've heard about it.
- Have you?

1646
01:21:13,283 --> 01:21:15,353
I'll give you a brief summary of the story.

1647
01:21:15,453 --> 01:21:18,523
"The Wizard of Oz" is about four friends...

1648
01:21:19,523 --> 01:21:22,092
who are on the journey to meet Oz,

1649
01:21:22,093 --> 01:21:25,563
the great wizard, to make their wishes.

1650
01:21:25,793 --> 01:21:26,893
The story begins...

1651
01:21:27,223 --> 01:21:30,493
at the house of a girl named Dorothy.

1652
01:21:30,993 --> 01:21:35,432
One day, a tornado strikes the village where Dorothy lives.

1653
01:21:35,433 --> 01:21:37,072
- Actually...
- Dorothy lived in Mungyeong.

1654
01:21:37,073 --> 01:21:38,642
And a tornado struck Mungyeong.

1655
01:21:38,643 --> 01:21:40,303
That's right. You can understand it like that.

1656
01:21:40,643 --> 01:21:43,913
But today, the tornado is stronger than ever.

1657
01:21:44,273 --> 01:21:45,813
It is so strong...

1658
01:21:45,913 --> 01:21:49,053
that it blows Dorothy's house away.

1659
01:21:49,513 --> 01:21:51,113
This is what we'll do today.

1660
01:21:51,523 --> 01:21:54,483
Mr. Choi will play Dorothy for us.

1661
01:21:54,583 --> 01:21:57,293
You will become the tornado...

1662
01:21:57,793 --> 01:22:00,662
and blow Mr. Choi's house away.

1663
01:22:00,663 --> 01:22:03,863
We'll create that scene today. Are you excited?

1664
01:22:03,963 --> 01:22:05,333
- Yes!
- Yes. Sounds fun.

1665
01:22:05,433 --> 01:22:07,733
Okay. When Dorothy comes home...

1666
01:22:07,833 --> 01:22:10,203
and says, "I'm home,"

1667
01:22:10,303 --> 01:22:11,903
the tornado will take action...

1668
01:22:12,003 --> 01:22:14,202
- and blow his house away.
- Blow me away!

1669
01:22:14,203 --> 01:22:15,512
Let's blow Dorothy away!

1670
01:22:15,513 --> 01:22:17,043
Let's blow the potato away!

1671
01:22:18,143 --> 01:22:20,742
Okay, Tornado. Get ready.

1672
01:22:20,743 --> 01:22:23,383
Should we watch Dorothy and wait for the signal?

1673
01:22:25,253 --> 01:22:27,052
Gosh. What a long day today.

1674
01:22:27,053 --> 01:22:28,893
I'll go home and have some chicken.

1675
01:22:29,653 --> 01:22:31,353
Gosh. What was the passcode?

1676
01:22:31,563 --> 01:22:33,762
Beep, beep. Clicking.

1677
01:22:33,763 --> 01:22:34,793
Beep-beep.

1678
01:22:35,293 --> 01:22:37,333
Gosh. I'm home!

1679
01:22:39,563 --> 01:22:42,702
Guys. It's not a person, but a house.

1680
01:22:42,703 --> 01:22:43,872
Let's step back a little.

1681
01:22:43,873 --> 01:22:45,873
Okay. Blow it away!

1682
01:22:46,603 --> 01:22:48,242
- Until Dorothy moves.
- I think I hit Mr. Choi.

1683
01:22:48,243 --> 01:22:49,873
Until Dorothy shakes.

1684
01:22:50,973 --> 01:22:52,042
Which way should I fly to?

1685
01:22:52,043 --> 01:22:54,283
- Which wind is strong?
- Try making sounds too.

1686
01:22:56,513 --> 01:22:58,252
- Goodness!
- Gosh. It's flying away!

1687
01:22:58,253 --> 01:23:00,353
(In the end, Dorothy is carried away by the tornado.)

1688
01:23:00,983 --> 01:23:01,993
How was it, everyone?

1689
01:23:02,093 --> 01:23:04,053
- It was fun.
- It's so simple, isn't it?

1690
01:23:04,153 --> 01:23:06,162
- Yes.
- You just...

1691
01:23:06,163 --> 01:23:08,993
created a scene for a play.

1692
01:23:09,233 --> 01:23:11,662
We'll keep making scenes 1 by 1 like this.

1693
01:23:11,663 --> 01:23:13,202
- How was it? Was it fun?
- Yes.

1694
01:23:13,203 --> 01:23:15,433
In that case, who wants to be Dorothy?

1695
01:23:15,733 --> 01:23:18,673
- Anyone who wants to play Dorothy?
- Who wants to be Dorothy this time?

1696
01:23:18,903 --> 01:23:20,072
Do you want to try it, Eun Soo?

1697
01:23:20,073 --> 01:23:22,212
No!

1698
01:23:22,213 --> 01:23:24,782
Why not? It's nothing. I'll help you by your side.

1699
01:23:24,783 --> 01:23:25,783
No!

1700
01:23:25,783 --> 01:23:26,783
(Strictly)

1701
01:23:27,043 --> 01:23:28,043
No.

1702
01:23:28,383 --> 01:23:29,483
Hold on!

1703
01:23:29,583 --> 01:23:31,782
- Good job.
- Ju Eun, let's go inside the house.

1704
01:23:31,783 --> 01:23:33,783
- Let's go inside.
- Yes!

1705
01:23:34,753 --> 01:23:35,892
It's a house.

1706
01:23:35,893 --> 01:23:37,153
- Yes.
- Do you want to sit here?

1707
01:23:37,453 --> 01:23:39,463
The light is off.

1708
01:23:40,823 --> 01:23:44,092
(The room is full in no time.)

1709
01:23:44,093 --> 01:23:45,103
Bye.

1710
01:23:45,563 --> 01:23:47,733
What about you? Do you need help?

1711
01:23:48,403 --> 01:23:49,602
Goodness. There's a jumping rope.

1712
01:23:49,603 --> 01:23:50,603
Do you want to do more?

1713
01:23:50,604 --> 01:23:52,173
(Ms. Kim prepares for the 2nd period.)

1714
01:23:54,473 --> 01:23:56,113
- Kyung Mo.
- Yes?

1715
01:23:56,213 --> 01:23:58,343
- Should we put this back on?
- What?

1716
01:23:58,643 --> 01:23:59,643
- Right.
- It fell off.

1717
01:24:00,313 --> 01:24:02,712
You must have played the tornado really hard, right?

1718
01:24:02,713 --> 01:24:03,713
(She puts on the name tag that fell off.)

1719
01:24:04,653 --> 01:24:06,422
- Thank you.
- It's done.

1720
01:24:06,423 --> 01:24:08,793
I'll take it off for you later. Don't do it yourself, Kyung Mo.

1721
01:24:09,493 --> 01:24:10,653
You like soccer, don't you?

1722
01:24:11,523 --> 01:24:13,522
We watch baseball more.

1723
01:24:13,523 --> 01:24:14,722
Baseball? Which team?

1724
01:24:14,723 --> 01:24:16,532
- I'm a Lotte's fan.
- Lotte?

1725
01:24:16,533 --> 01:24:18,402
- Which team do you root for?
- KT, right?

1726
01:24:18,403 --> 01:24:21,032
I just watch it from time to time.

1727
01:24:21,033 --> 01:24:22,202
(On the contrary,)

1728
01:24:22,203 --> 01:24:24,473
- I'm a Lotte's fan.
- Lotte?

1729
01:24:24,673 --> 01:24:25,902
- Lotte.
- Hurry.

1730
01:24:25,903 --> 01:24:28,043
(Mr. Choi is talking to the students.)

1731
01:24:32,183 --> 01:24:37,153
(She gets started on her own in her haste.)

1732
01:24:40,623 --> 01:24:42,892
- Let's go, Potato Teacher.
- Let's go.

1733
01:24:42,893 --> 01:24:44,292
Let's go, Potato Teacher!

1734
01:24:44,293 --> 01:24:46,363
- Can we play baseball?
- As for baseball...

1735
01:24:46,463 --> 01:24:48,063
What? Mr. Choi is going out.

1736
01:24:52,663 --> 01:24:53,663
(Before she stops him,)

1737
01:24:53,663 --> 01:24:54,663
Can we play it?

1738
01:24:54,664 --> 01:24:56,472
I have to get changed, then. But the break is short.

1739
01:24:56,473 --> 01:24:57,473
That's right.

1740
01:24:57,474 --> 01:24:58,542
Goodness.

1741
01:24:58,543 --> 01:25:03,013
(Mr. Choi went out to play with the kids.)

1742
01:25:04,443 --> 01:25:06,783
Gosh. I can't believe this. I'm doing it alone.

1743
01:25:10,953 --> 01:25:15,093
(Next episode)

1744
01:25:16,153 --> 01:25:18,223
(I don't know what you mean, Hyun Wook.)

1745
01:25:18,723 --> 01:25:22,132
(I don't know what you liked and what you didn't,)

1746
01:25:22,133 --> 01:25:23,793
(but I think I did my job.)

1747
01:25:23,993 --> 01:25:25,303
At that place, I...

1748
01:25:28,003 --> 01:25:31,033
(Nothing you did satisfied me 100 percent.)

1749
01:25:32,273 --> 01:25:34,503
(How can I satisfy you 100 percent?)

1750
01:25:36,513 --> 01:25:38,443
Who can satisfy you completely?

1751
01:25:38,743 --> 01:25:39,843
Who would?

1752
01:25:42,013 --> 01:25:46,553
(What will happen at the end of the fierce argument?)

1753
01:25:58,802 --> 01:26:00,802
Dramaday.me
